%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fone-nation-one-election-fourth-committee%5C%22%3Ea%20committee%20has%20been%20set%20up%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20deliberate%20the%20matter.%20Surprisingly%2C%20a%20former%20president%20of%20India%20is%20its%20chairperson.%20This%20is%20to%20lend%20greater%20weight%20to%20the%20recommendations%20of%20the%20committee%2C%20given%20the%20contentious%20nature%20of%20the%20proposal.%20The%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcommittee-on-simultaneous-polls%5C%22%3Edeclined%20to%20join%20the%20committee%3C%2Fa%3E.%20So%2C%20the%20opposition%20view%20will%20go%20unrepresented.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBJP%E2%80%99s%20gambit%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20sees%20the%20move%20as%20politically%20advantageous.%20It%20hopes%20to%20cash%20in%20on%20the%20popularity%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20to%20win%20not%20only%20the%20national%20elections%20but%20also%20the%20assembly%20elections%2C%20several%20of%20which%20it%20has%20lost%20recently.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20possibly%20believes%20that%20in%20a%20national%20election%2C%20national%20issues%20predominate%20rather%20than%20local%20ones%2C%20and%20that%20this%20would%20sway%20voters%20to%20vote%20for%20the%20BJP.%20In%20assembly%20elections%2C%20it%20has%20often%20called%20for%20%E2%80%98Double%20engine%20%3Cem%3Eki%20sarkar%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20but%20it%20has%20not%20worked%20at%20times.%20Depending%20on%20the%20situation%2C%20people%20may%20focus%20on%20local%20issues%20even%20in%20a%20simultaneous%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20there%20are%20basic%20issues%20that%20need%20to%20be%20considered%2C%20like%20the%20consequences%20for%20the%20federal%20structure%20of%20the%20country%20and%20its%20impact%20on%20the%20already%20fraying%20political%20and%20economic%20democracy%20in%20the%20country.%20Hopefully%2C%20the%20committee%20will%20take%20into%20account%20these%20long-term%20implications%20for%20the%20nation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fone-nation-one-election-one-leader-one-faith-one-business-house%5C%22%3EOne%20Nation%2C%20One%20Election%2C%20One%20Leader%2C%20One%20Faith%2C%20One%20Business%20House%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECost%20of%20elections%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20issue%20is%20framed%20as%20a%20practical%2C%20economic%20one%20%E2%80%93%20namely%2C%20that%20having%20one%20election%20every%20five%20years%20will%20reduce%20the%20cost%20of%20elections.%20Costs%20are%20both%20direct%20%E2%80%93%20holding%20repeated%20elections%20%E2%80%93%20and%20indirect%20%E2%80%93%20due%20to%20delays%20in%20the%20implementation%20and%20announcement%20of%20policies.%20It%20is%20said%20that%20elections%20force%20ruling%20parties%20to%20go%20for%20%E2%80%98populist%E2%80%99%20policies%20that%20are%20fiscally%20imprudent%20and%20hence%20undesirable.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20election%20expenditures%20of%20candidates%20have%20snowballed%2C%20running%20into%20thousands%20of%20crores.%20Recently%2C%20in%20a%20poll-bound%20state%2C%20a%20politician%20told%20this%20author%20that%20for%20a%20serious%20MLA%20candidate%2C%20an%20election%20campaign%20will%20cost%20around%20Rs%205%20-6%20crore%2C%20and%20for%20an%20MP%2C%20no%20less%20than%20Rs%2030%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAssuming%20at%20least%20two%20serious%20candidates%20per%20constituency%20and%20adding%20to%20this%20the%20cost%20of%20holding%20the%20elections%2C%20the%20total%20figure%20for%20the%20country%20would%20approach%20Rs%201%20lakh%20crore.%20For%20an%20economy%20with%20a%20GDP%20of%20about%20Rs%20300%20lakh%20crore%2C%20it%20amounts%20to%200.33%25%20of%20the%20GDP.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20the%20direct%20cost%20is%20not%20too%20much.%20What%20is%20the%20indirect%20cost%3F%20That%20is%20hard%20to%20estimate%20since%20there%20are%20both%20tangible%20and%20intangible%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20months%20before%20an%20election%20in%20a%20state%2C%20the%20leadership%20gets%20busy%20campaigning%2C%20diverting%20their%20attention%20from%20serious%20national%20and%20local%20issues.%20With%20four%20to%20five%20major%20elections%20each%20year%20in%20the%20five-year%20cycle%2C%20major%20political%20parties%20are%20constantly%20busy%20preparing%20for%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20attract%20voters%2C%20they%20offer%20goodies%20and%20concessions%20which%20add%20to%20the%20fiscal%20burden%2C%20like%20subsidies%20on%20gas%20cylinders%2C%20cheap%20or%20free%20grains%2C%20and%20water%2C%20electricity%20and%20cash%20to%20farmers%20and%20women%20heads%20of%20households.%20These%20add%20up%20to%20a%20few%20lakh%20crores%20every%20year%2C%20perhaps%201-2%25%20of%20the%20GDP%20depending%20on%20what%20is%20counted.%20Again%2C%20the%20cost%20is%20not%20too%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECompared%20to%20this%2C%20what%20the%20well-off%20get%20as%20tax%20cuts%20is%20far%20greater.%20The%20cut%20in%20corporation%20tax%20in%202019%20immediately%20cost%20Rs%201.6%20lakh%20crore.%20Wealth%20tax%20etc.%20if%20collected%20could%20yield%202-3%25%20of%20the%20GDP.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fnarendra-modi-revdi-freebies-economy-politics%5C%22%3ERevdinomics%20Isn%E2%80%99t%20About%20the%20Economy%2C%20Stupid%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhy%20do%20political%20parties%20need%20to%20offer%20%E2%80%98freebies%E2%80%99%3F%20People%20getting%20them%20are%20called%20%3Cem%3Elabhartis%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Hindi%20for%20beneficiaries).%20Is%20this%20not%20like%20bribing%20voters%3F%20And%2C%20is%20it%20not%20a%20failure%20of%20democracy%20that%20the%20public%20chooses%20its%20representatives%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20who%20offers%20more%20inducements%20before%20elections%3F%20Can%20such%20elections%2C%20which%20are%20supposed%20to%20sustain%20democracy%2C%20be%20desirable%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDemocracy%20weakens%20when%20the%20people%E2%80%99s%20choice%20is%20not%20based%20on%20who%20will%20represent%20their%20interests%20and%20fulfil%20their%20aspirations.%20Actually%2C%20people%20are%20helpless%20and%20have%20lost%20faith%20that%20their%20representatives%20and%20political%20parties%20will%20deliver%20on%20promises.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETwo%20years%20ago%2C%20at%20a%20meeting%20of%20an%20opposition%20party%20to%20help%20with%20their%20election%20manifesto%2C%20the%20party%20people%20asked%20towards%20the%20end%20of%20the%20discussion%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20are%20we%20offering%20the%20people%20today%3F%E2%80%9D%20Long%20and%20medium-run%20programmes%20are%20only%20decorative.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDemocracy%20as%20process%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDemocracy%20is%20always%20in%20a%20state%20of%20flux%20and%20not%20in%20its%20ideal%20form.%20It%20can%20be%20weakening%20or%20strengthening.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20strengthen%20democracy%2C%20politics%20needs%20to%20be%20more%20accountable.%20But%20this%20does%20not%20appear%20to%20be%20the%20principal%20motivation%20for%20the%20people%E2%80%99s%20vote.%20It%20can%20be%20swayed%20by%20a%20Pulwama%20or%20Balakot%2C%20a%20Bofors%2C%20or%20corruption%20and%20inflation%20during%20UPA-II.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOften%2C%20the%20choice%20is%20for%20the%20lesser%20evil.%20Vested%20interests%20that%20control%20political%20parties%20take%20advantage%20of%20this%20weakness%20to%20push%20their%20agenda.%20This%20undermines%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHaving%20one%20election%20every%20five%20years%20will%20make%20political%20parties%20more%20unaccountable%20and%20free%20to%20fulfil%20the%20agenda%20of%20vested%20interests.%20That%20will%20weaken%20democracy%20and%20cost%20the%20nation%20far%20more%20than%20the%20direct%20and%20indirect%20costs%20of%20elections%20at%20present.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20weakness%20of%20democracy%20makes%20elections%20so%20expensive.%20People%20are%20not%20enthused%20by%20the%20performance%20of%20candidates.%20To%20counter%20that%2C%20mega%20rallies%2C%20hoardings%20and%20posters%20in%20large%20numbers%20are%20put%20up.%20Vote%20banks%20are%20created%20and%20nurtured.%20Now%2C%20there%20are%20additional%20expenditures%20on%20social%20media%2C%20troll%20armies%2C%20the%20manipulation%20of%20electoral%20rolls%2C%20etc.%20Workers%20and%20crowds%20are%20hired%20and%20money%20and%20goodies%20are%20distributed%20in%20the%20last%20three%20days%20before%20election%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAll%20this%20requires%20large%20sums%20of%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthe-show-must-go-off%5C%22%3EThe%20Show%20Must%20Go%20Off%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20money%20spent%20is%20way%20above%20the%20allowed%20election%20expenditure%2C%20so%20it%20has%20to%20be%20black%2Fillegal.%20What%20is%20obtained%20through%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftag%2Felectoral-bonds%5C%22%3Eelectoral%20bonds%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20peanuts%20compared%20to%20the%20actual%20expenditures.%20It%20also%20goes%20mostly%20to%20the%20ruling%20party%20and%20is%20like%20a%20bribe%20in%20white.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20collection%20of%20illegal%20funds%20leads%20to%20the%20emergence%20of%20a%20close%20nexus%20between%20politicians%20and%20vested%20interests.%20Not%20only%20does%20this%20undermine%20democracy%2C%20but%20also%20subverts%20policy%2C%20and%20in%20a%20vicious%20cycle%20leads%20to%20the%20further%20proliferation%20of%20the%20black%20economy%20and%20the%20weakening%20of%20democracy.%20This%20weakening%20of%20democracy%20is%20the%20real%20cost%20to%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBenefits%20outweigh%20the%20costs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201993%2C%20a%20top%20bureaucrat%20in%20the%20government%20argued%20that%20the%20government%20could%20do%20what%20it%20pleased%20for%20the%20first%20two-and-a-half%20years%20but%20must%20pursue%20populist%20policies%20after%20that.%20So%2C%20tough%20anti-people%20policies%20can%20be%20pursued%20in%20the%20first%20period.%20Cynically%2C%20it%20implies%20that%20the%20public%20is%20gullible%20and%20can%20be%20fooled%20%E2%80%93%20a%20line%20that%20political%20parties%20have%20internalised.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20all%20elections%20are%20held%20together%20once%20in%20five%20years%2C%20people-friendly%20policies%20will%20be%20pursued%20only%20for%20short%20periods%20of%20time%2C%20unlike%20now%2C%20when%20ruling%20parties%20have%20to%20be%20on%20their%20toes%20most%20of%20the%20time.%20When%20in%20spite%20of%20such%20constant%20scrutiny%20the%20fruits%20of%20development%20have%20mostly%20been%20cornered%20by%20the%20well-off%20sections%2C%20imagine%20how%20much%20worse%20it%20will%20get%20with%20elections%20once%20in%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20undemocratic%20content%20of%20policies%20will%20dominate%20and%20the%20alienation%20of%20the%20marginalised%20will%20grow%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20further%20erosion%20of%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENot%20even%20in%20a%20perfect%20democracy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20India%20had%20a%20perfect%20democracy%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98One%20Nation%2C%20One%20Election%E2%80%99%20idea%20assumes%20homogeneity%20in%20the%20nation.%20India%20is%20diverse%2C%20with%20different%20regions%20confronting%20diverse%20issues%2C%20and%20that%20impacts%20politics%20in%20the%20states%20and%20the%20election%20schedule.%20So%2C%20a%20one-size-fits-all%20approach%20goes%20against%20the%20reality%20of%20the%20nation%E2%80%99s%20diversity%20and%20can%20lead%20to%20severe%20political%20backlash.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELessons%20need%20to%20be%20drawn%20from%20the%20experience%20of%20the%20initial%20years%20after%20independence%2C%20when%20one%20party%20ruled%20in%20the%20Centre%20and%20the%20states.%20The%20ruling%20party%20is%20going%20one%20step%20further%20to%20homogenise%20the%20country%20through%20%E2%80%98one%20nation%20one%20this%20or%20that%E2%80%99%20and%20this%20is%20dangerous.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20brief%2C%20the%20reality%20is%20that%20India%20has%20an%20imperfect%20democracy%20that%20needs%20to%20be%20strengthened.%20Elections%20are%20the%20times%20when%20the%20public%20can%20force%20political%20parties%20to%20become%20answerable.%20So%2C%20repeated%20elections%20have%20a%20cost%2C%20but%20the%20benefits%20of%20enhanced%20democracy%20that%20they%20trigger%20are%20far%20greater.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIdeas%20are%20from%20the%20author%E2%80%99s%20book%2C%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fem%3EUnderstanding%20the%20Black%20Economy%20and%20Black%20Money%E2%80%A6%E2%80%99%3Cem%3E%2C%202017%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Farun-kumar%5C%22%3EArun%20Kumar%3C%2Fa%3E%20retired%20as%20professor%20of%20economics%2C%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697160614000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F10%2F28114631%2F2020_10img28_Oct_2020_PTI28-10-2020_000030B.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fone-nation-one-election-further-weaken-democracy%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20argument%20is%20that%20repeated%20polls%20are%20expensive%20and%20also%20push%20political%20parties%20towards%20populistic%20promises.%20But%20the%20long%20term%20benefits%20they%20trigger%20might%20be%20greater.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fone-nation-one-election-further-weaken-democracy%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Updates%3A%20As%20Israel%20Bombards%20Gaza%2C%20Over%204%20Lakh%20Forced%20To%20Flee%20Homes%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20423%2C000%20people%20have%20been%20forced%20to%20flee%20their%20homes%20in%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20the%20United%20Nations%20said%2C%20f