i%3E%20%3Cli%3EOne%20of%20the%20officers%20who%20arrested%20him%20was%20found%20guilty%20on%20Thursday%20of%20criminally%20negligent%20homicide.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EBody%20camera%20footage%20showed%20officers%20putting%20McClain%20in%20a%20Carotid%20hold.%20Paramedics%20injected%20him%20with%20ketamine.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EJurors%20convicted%20a%20Denver-area%20police%20officer%20Thursday%20and%20acquitted%20another%20of%20charges%20in%20the%202019%20death%20of%20Elijah%20McClain%2C%20a%20Black%20man%20whose%20name%20became%20a%20rallying%20cry%20in%20protests%20over%20racial%20injustice%20in%20policing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAurora%20police%20officer%20Randy%20Roedema%20was%20found%20guilty%20of%20criminally%20negligent%20homicide%20and%20third-degree%20assault.%20The%2012-person%20jury%20found%20officer%20Jason%20Rosenblatt%20not%20guilty%20on%20all%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcClain's%20mother%2C%20Sheneen%20McClain%2C%20listened%20to%20the%20verdict%20from%20the%20front%20row%2C%20where%20Attorney%20General%20Phil%20Weiser%20had%20his%20hand%20on%20her%20shoulder.%20She%20held%20her%20right%20hand%20high%20in%20a%20raised%20fist%20as%20she%20left%20the%20courtroom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcClain%20died%20after%20being%20put%20in%20a%20neck%20hold%20by%20a%20third%20officer%20and%20pinned%20to%20the%20ground%2C%20then%20injected%20by%20paramedics%20with%20an%20overdose%20of%20ketamine.%20The%20third%20officer%20and%20two%20paramedics%20are%20awaiting%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20initially%20did%20not%20receive%20widespread%20attention%2C%20but%20protests%20over%20the%20killing%20of%20George%20Floyd%20the%20following%20year%20sparked%20outrage%20over%20McClain's%20death.%20His%20pleading%20words%20captured%20on%20body%20camera%20footage%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20an%20introvert%20and%20I'm%20different%2C%26quot%3B%20struck%20a%20chord.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20local%20prosecutor%20in%202019%20decided%20against%20criminal%20charges%20because%20the%20coroner's%20office%20could%20not%20determine%20exactly%20how%20the%2023-year-old%20massage%20therapist%20died.%20But%20Colorado%20Gov.%20Jared%20Polis%20ordered%20state%20Attorney%20General%20Phil%20Weiser's%20office%20to%20take%20another%20look%20at%20the%20case%20in%202020%2C%20and%20the%20officers%20and%20paramedics%20were%20indicted%20in%202021%20by%20a%20grand%20jury.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20killings%20of%20McClain%2C%20Floyd%20and%20others%20triggered%20a%20wave%20of%20legislation%20that%20put%20limits%20on%20the%20use%20of%20neck%20holds%20in%20more%20than%20two%20dozen%20states.%20Colorado%20now%20tells%20paramedics%20not%20to%20give%20ketamine%20to%20people%20suspected%20of%20having%20a%20controversial%20condition%20known%20as%20excited%20delirium%2C%20which%20has%20symptoms%20including%20increased%20strength%20that%20has%20been%20associated%20with%20racial%20bias%20against%20Black%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoedema%20and%20Rosenblatt%20did%20not%20testify%20in%20their%20defense%20at%20trial.%20Their%20attorneys%20blamed%20McClain's%20death%20on%20the%20paramedics%20for%20injecting%20him%20with%20ketamine%2C%20which%20doctors%20said%20is%20what%20ultimately%20killed%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20prosecutors%20argued%20that%20the%20officers'%20restraint%20of%20McClain%20contributed.%20Senior%20Assistant%20Attorney%20General%20Jason%20Slothouber%20told%20jurors%20that%20Roedema%20and%20Rosenblatt%20also%20encouraged%20the%20paramedics%20to%20give%20McClain%20ketamine%20by%20describing%20him%20as%20having%20symptoms%20of%20excited%20delirium%20that%20they%20had%20learned%20about%20in%20training.%20But%20he%20said%20the%20officers%20did%20not%20tell%20them%20anything%20about%20McClain's%20complaints%20that%20he%20could%20not%20breathe%2C%20something%20prosecutors%20said%20happened%20six%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESheneen%20McClain%20sat%20with%20attorneys%20for%20the%20state%20in%20the%20front%20row%20of%20the%20courtroom%20during%20the%20trial%2C%20part%20of%20her%20quest%20to%20remind%20the%20mostly%20white%20jury%20that%20her%20son%20was%20a%20real%20person.%20She%20watched%20the%20encounter%20being%20played%20over%20and%20over%20again%20along%20with%20graphic%20photos%20from%20his%20autopsy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20testimony%20that%20stretched%20over%20three%20weeks%2C%20witnesses%20were%20limited%20to%20offering%20what%20they%20%26quot%3Bperceived%26quot%3B%20someone%20to%20be%20doing%20or%20saying%20in%20the%20video.%20The%20video%20clips%20did%20not%20always%20provide%20a%20complete%20picture%20of%20what%20was%20happening%2C%20but%20Judge%20Mark%20Warner%20said%20the%20jurors%20were%20the%20only%20ones%20who%20could%20decide%20what%20they%20meant%2C%20just%20like%20any%20other%20piece%20of%20evidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20emotional%20weight%20of%20McClain's%20last%20words%20captured%20on%20body%20camera%20and%20a%20story%20about%20him%20playing%20the%20violin%20in%20an%20animal%20shelter%2C%20the%20trial%20did%20not%20include%20much%20testimony%20about%20him%20or%20his%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20co-worker%20at%20a%20massage%20studio%20testified%20briefly%20about%20how%20he%20used%20to%20bike%20or%20run%20miles%20to%20work%20in%20an%20affluent%20suburb%20and%20then%20also%20run%20on%20lunch%20breaks.%20A%20photograph%20of%20a%20smiling%20McClain%20she%20took%20shortly%20before%20his%20death%20was%20shown%20to%20jurors%20during%20closing%20arguments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcClain%20was%20stopped%20Aug.%2024%2C%202019%2C%20while%20walking%20home%20from%20a%20convenience%20store%20on%20a%20summer%20night%2C%20listening%20to%20music%20and%20wearing%20a%20mask%20that%20covered%20most%20of%20his%20face.%20A%20911%20caller%20reported%20him%20as%20suspicious%2C%20and%20the%20police%20stop%20quickly%20became%20physical%20after%20McClain%2C%20seemingly%20caught%20off%20guard%2C%20asked%20to%20be%20left%20alone.%20He%20had%20not%20been%20accused%20of%20committing%20any%20crime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20encounter%20quickly%20escalated%2C%20with%20Officers%20Nathan%20Woodyard%2C%20Roedema%20and%20Rosenblatt%20taking%20McClain%20to%20the%20ground%2C%20and%20Woodyard%20putting%20him%20in%20a%20neck%20hold%20and%20pressing%20against%20his%20carotid%20artery%2C%20temporarily%20rendering%20him%20unconscious.%20The%20officers%20told%20investigators%20they%20took%20McClain%20down%20after%20hearing%20Roedema%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BHe%20grabbed%20your%20gun%20dude.%26quot%3B%20He%20later%20said%20Rosenblatt's%20gun%20was%20the%20target.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20initial%20statement%20was%20heard%20on%20the%20body%20camera%20footage%20but%20exactly%20what%20happened%20is%20difficult%20to%20see.%20The%20prosecution%20urged%20jurors%20to%20be%20skeptical%2C%20saying%20Rosenblatt%20said%20he%20could%20not%20feel%20anyone%20reaching%20for%20his%20gun.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20one%20of%20Roedema's%20defense%20lawyers%2C%20Don%20Sisson%2C%20pointed%20out%20that%20McClain%20said%20%26quot%3BI%20intend%20to%20take%20my%20power%20back%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20he%20argued%20showed%20intent.%20The%20officers%20had%20to%20act%20in%20the%20moment%20to%20protect%20themselves%2C%20according%20to%20Sisson.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20didn't%20get%20to%20watch%20the%20video%20over%20and%20over%20and%20over%20for%20three%20weeks%20before%20they%20get%20to%20act%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParamedics%20injected%20McClain%20with%20ketamine%20as%20Roedema%20and%20another%20officer%20who%20was%20not%20charged%20held%20him%20on%20the%20ground.%20He%20went%20into%20cardiac%20arrest%20en%20route%20to%20the%20hospital%20and%20died%20three%20days%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERosenblatt's%20lawyer%2C%20Harvey%20Steinberg%2C%20said%20his%20client%2C%20the%20most%20junior%20officer%20on%20scene%2C%20was%20a%20scapegoat%20in%20a%20prosecution%20driven%20by%20politics.%20He%20pointed%20out%20that%20Rosenblatt%20was%20not%20restraining%20McClain%20when%20the%20ketamine%20was%20given.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20grand%20jury%20was%20convened%