est-supercarrier-deployment-unexpected-turn-israel-crisis-2023-10%5C%22%3Earrived%20in%20the%20eastern%20Mediterranean%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20officials%20announced%20the%20movement%20of%20the%20carrier%20strike%20group%20toward%20Israel%20on%20Sunday%2C%20the%20day%20after%20Hamas%20carried%20out%20deadly%20terror%20attacks%20against%20the%20US%20ally.%20The%20Ford's%20sudden%20retasking%20was%20presented%20as%20a%20sign%20of%20US%20support%20for%20Israel%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20deterrent%20%E2%80%94%20a%20common%20task%20for%20aircraft%20carriers%2C%20which%20have%20long%20been%20used%20to%20project%20American%20military%20power.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ships%20sailing%20with%20the%20Ford%20include%20the%20Ticonderoga-class%20guided-missile%20cruiser%20USS%20Normandy%20and%20the%20Arleigh-Burke-class%20guided-missile%20destroyers%20USS%20Thomas%20Hudner%2C%20USS%20Ramage%2C%20USS%20Carney%2C%20and%20USS%20Roosevelt.%20The%20amount%20of%20firepower%20each%20vessel%20brings%20adds%20up%2C%20especially%20considering%20the%20capabilities%20of%20the%20air%20wing%20aboard%20USS%20Gerald%20R.%20Ford.%20With%20these%20ships%2C%20the%20US%20is%20sending%20a%20clear%20and%20intimidating%20message%20amid%20a%20serious%20international%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20senior%20US%20defense%20official%20said%20Thursday%20that%20this%20force%20posture%20sends%20this%20message%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20United%20States%20is%20unequivocal%20in%20its%20support%20for%20the%20defense%20of%20Israel%20and%20is%20sending%20a%20warning%20to%20any%20entities%20that%20would%20consider%20taking%20advantage%20of%20this%20conflict%20and%20this%20war%20to%20escalate%20violence.%20One%20word%2C%20quite%20simply%3A%20Don't.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarrier%20strike%20groups%20%26quot%3Bare%20a%20self-contained%20unit%20that%20can%20strike%20targets%201%2C000%20miles%20away%20%E2%80%94%20farther%20with%20aerial%20refueling%20%E2%80%94%20can%20defend%20against%20air%2C%20missile%2C%20and%20submarine%20attack%2C%20and%20can%20maintain%20maritime%20security%20over%20an%20area%20of%20hundreds%20of%20square%20miles%2C%26quot%3B%20Bryan%20Clark%2C%20a%20former%20US%20Navy%20officer%20and%20defense%20expert%20at%20the%20Hudson%20Institute%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223344%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20world's%20largest%20aircraft%20carrier%20USS%20Gerald%20R.%20Ford%20(CVN%2078)%20and%20Ticonderoga-class%20guided-missile%20cruiser%20USS%20Normandy%20(CG%2060)%20steam%20in%20formation%20in%20the%20Ionian%20Sea%2C%20Aug.%2020%2C%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65284b3055f52b01b35e5396%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222508%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20world's%20largest%20aircraft%20carrier%20USS%20Gerald%20R.%20Ford%20(CVN%2078)%20and%20Ticonderoga-class%20guided-missile%20cruiser%20USS%20Normandy%20(CG%2060)%20steam%20in%20formation%20in%20the%20Ionian%20Sea%2C%20Aug.%2020%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EUS%20Navy%20Photo%20by%20Mass%20Communication%20Specialist%203rd%20Class%20Maxwell%20Orlosky%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20USS%20Gerald%20R.%20Ford%20was%20commissioned%20over%20five%20years%20ago%20and%20was%20in%20development%20for%20more%20than%20a%20decade.%20The%20price%20tag%20of%20the%20first-in-class%20carrier%2C%20often%20over%20budget%20and%20behind%20schedule%20during%20its%20development%2C%20was%20a%20whopping%20%2413%20billion.%20It%20set%20out%20on%20a%20short%20maiden%20deployment%20last%20year%20and%20its%20first%20full%20deployment%20as%20part%20of%20a%20fully%20certified%20carrier%20strike%20group%20earlier%20this%20year.%20That%20deployment%20is%20ongoing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20challenges%20in%20fielding%20the%20carrier%2C%20the%20Ford%20represents%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-admiral-navy-too-much-new-tech-aircraft-carrier-ford-2021-8%5C%22%3Econsiderable%20upgrade%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20previous%20Nimitz-class%20aircraft%20carriers.%20It%20boasts%20faster%20aircraft%20sorties%20and%20a%20smaller%20crew%2C%20with%20the%20Electromagnetic%20Aircraft%20Launch%20System%20(EMALS)%20and%20Advanced%20Arresting%20Gear%20(AAG)%20allowing%20fixed-wing%20aircraft%20to%20launch%20more%20smoothly%20and%20effectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Ford's%20electromagnetic%20catapult%20and%20arresting%20gear%20allow%20it%20to%20launch%20and%20recover%20aircraft%20faster%20than%20other%20carriers%2C%26quot%3B%20Clark%20said.%20He%20added%20that%20those%20capabilities%20may%20have%20less%20of%20an%20impact%20in%20the%20Pacific%20Ocean%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20the%20flights%20are%20so%20long%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20in%20areas%20like%20the%20eastern%20Mediterranean%2C%20%26quot%3Bbeing%20able%20to%20rapidly%20launch%20aircraft%20could%20enable%20the%20Ford%20to%20respond%20to%20air%20threats%20much%20faster%20than%20even%20ground-based%20aircraft.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Ford%20is%20operating%20with%20eight%20squadrons%20of%20attack%20and%20support%20aircraft%2C%20per%20US%20Central%20Command.%20Carrier%20Airwing%208%20is%20tasked%20with%20defense%20of%20the%20carrier%20and%20conducting%20sustained%20air%20operations%20and%20consists%20of%20aviation%20assets%20such%20as%20multirole%20F%2FA-18E%2FF%20Super%20Hornets%2C%20electronic%20warfare%20EA-18G%20Growlers%2C%20early%20warning%20planes%20like%20the%20E-2D%20Hawkeye%2C%20and%20rotary%20aircraft.%20Carrier%20air%20wings%20typically%20have%20more%20than%2070%20aircraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20carrier's%20new%20technologies%2C%20the%20dual-band%20radar%2C%20capable%20of%20operating%20two%20frequency%20ranges%2C%20is%20also%20a%20major%20boon%20for%20operations%20and%20logistics%2C%20bolstering%20air%20defenses%20and%20surveillance.%20And%20the%20Ford's%20advanced%20weapons%20elevators%20were%20designed%20to%20transport%20larger%20and%20more%20complex%20munitions%20and%20systems%20much%20quicker%20to%20the%20flight%20deck%2C%20enabling%20the%20fast%20operations%20for%20which%20the%20carrier%20Ford%20was%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222133%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20E%2FA-18G%20Growler%20attached%20to%20the%20%26quot%3BGray%20Wolves%26quot%3B%20of%20Electronic%20Attack%20Squadron%20(VAQ)%20142%20takes%20off%20of%20the%20world's%20largest%20aircraft%20carrier%2C%20USS%20Gerald%20R.%20Ford%20(CVN%2078)%20during%20flight%20operations%20in%20the%20Adriatic%20Sea%2C%20Sept.%2013%2C%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65281e8f55f52b01b35e11bb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221422%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20E%2FA-18G%20Growler%20attached%20to%20the%20%26quot%3BGray%20Wolves%26quot%3B%20of%20Electronic%20Attack%20Squadron%20(VAQ)%20142%20takes%20off%20of%20the%20world's%20largest%20aircraft%20carrier%2C%20USS%20Gerald%20R.%20Ford%20(CVN%2078)%20during%20flight%20operations%20in%20the%20Adriatic%20Sea%2C%20Sept.%2013%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EU.S.%20Navy%20photo%20by%20Mass%20Communication%20Specialist%202nd%20Class%20Jackson%20Adkins%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Ticonderoga-class%20cruiser%20(CG)%20USS%20Normandy%20and%20four%20Arleigh-Burke-class%C2%A0destroyers%20(DDGs)%2C%20USS%20Thomas%20Hudner%2C%20USS%20Ramage%2C%20USS%20Carney%2C%20and%20USS%20Roosevelt%2C%20are%20also%20key%20to%20the%20strike%20group's%20combat%20power.%20Carrier%20groups%20can%20also%20be%20escorted%20by%20a%20submarine%2C%20though%20there%20hasn't%20been%20mention%20of%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20destroyers%20can%20carry%20top%20air%20defense%20interceptor%20missiles%20like%20the%20Standard%20Missile%206%20(SM-6)%2C%20Harpoon%20anti-ship%20missiles%2C%20and%20the%20medium-range%20Evolved%20Sea%20Sparrow%20Missile%2C%20and%20the%20DDGs%20and%20CG%20can%20both%20carry%20Tomahawk%20cruise%20missiles%20with%20substantial%20range%20that%20would%20allow%20the%20strike%20group%20to%20hit%20land-based%20targets%20of%20an%20Israeli%20adversary%20beyond%20the%20range%20of%20their%20anti-ship%20weapons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Pentagon%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.defense.gov%2FNews%2FReleases%2FRelease%2FArticle%2F3551716%2Fstatement-from-secretary-lloyd-j-austin-iii-on-us-force-posture-changes-in-the%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20carrier%20strike%20group%20was%20moved%20%26quot%3Bto%20strengthen%20Department%20of%20Defense%20posture%20in%20the%20region%20to%20bolster%20regional%20deterrence%20efforts%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20US%20Central%20Command%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuss-gerald-ford-supercarrier-strike-group-arrive-israel-hamas-war-2023-10%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20week%20its%20purpose%20is%20%26quot%3Bto%20deter%20any%20actor%20seeking%20to%20escalate%20the%20situation%20or%20widen%20this%20war%2C%26quot%3B%20referring%20to%20the%20ongoing%20fighting%20between%20Israel%20and%20Hamas%2C%20a%20Gaza-based%20militant%20group%20backed%20by%20Iran.%20The%20combat%20capability%20available%20in%20a%20strike%20group%20drives%20that%20message%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20that%20clear%20message%20could%20be%20even%20stronger.%20A%20British%20Royal%20Navy%20force%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuk-warships-aircraft-joining-us-navy-carrier-strike-group-israel-2023-10%5C%22%3Ewill%20be%20sent%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20the%20eastern%20Mediterranean%2C%20and%20reports%20say%20the%20US%20is%20considering%20the%20possibility%20of%20tasking%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-considering-sending-another-aircraft-carrier-near-israel-reports-2023-10%5C%22%3Esecond%20aircraft%20carrier%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20the%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20officials%20told%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20this%20week%20there%20have%20been%20conversations%20about%20sending%20USS%20Dwight%20D.%20Eisenhower%2C%20which%20will%20soon%20deploy%2C%20to%20the%20eastern%20Mediterranean%2C%20but%20it%20remains%20unclear%20if%20USS%20Eisenhower%20would%20replace%20the%20Ford%20or%20join%20its%20group.%20USS%20Eisenhower%20is%20setting%20sail%20this%20week%20for%20a%20deployment%20that%20was%20planned%20months%20ago%2C%20but%20the%20potential%20for%20the%20carrier%20to%20be%20redirected%20is%20always%20there.%20If%20the%20Eisenhower%20does%20join%20the%20Ford%2C%20it%20will%20be%20the%20first%20time%20two%20carriers%20have%20been%20deployed%20in%20the%20area%20since%20the%20March%202020%20Camp%20Taji%20incident%2C%20when%20three%20soldiers%20in%20the%20US-led%20coalition%20were%20killed%20by%20rockets%20fired%20against%20their%20base%20in%20Iraq.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Department%20of%20Defense%20declined%20to%20comment%20to%20Insider%20on%20whether%20there%20were%20conversations%20on%20tasking%20the%20Eisenhower%20with%20a%20mission%20outside%20its%20original%20deployment%20plans.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222336%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Lt.%20Bryan%20Goodman%2C%20left%2C%20from%20Wellington%2C%20Florida%2C%20and%20Chief%20Warrant%20Officer%203%20William%20Sum%2C%20from%20Panorama%20City%2C%20California%2C%20both%20assigned%20to%20the%20air%20department%20of%20the%20world's%20largest%20aircraft%20carrier%2C%20USS%20Gerald%20R.%20Ford%20(CVN%2078)%2C%20signal%20to%20launch%20an%20E-2D%20Hawkeye%20attached%20to%20the%20%26quot%3BBear%20Aces%26quot%3B%20of%20Airborne%20Command%20and%20Control%20Squadron%20(VAW)%20124%20during%20flight%20operations%20in%20the%20Adriatic%20Sea%2C%20Sept.%206%2C%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652827ba6561dd877e7925b3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221557%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELt.%20Bryan%20Goodman%2C%20left%2C%20from%20Wellington%2C%20Florida%2C%20and%20Chief%20Warrant%20Officer%203%20William%20Sum%2C%20from%20Panorama%20City%2C%20California%2C%20both%20assigned%20to%20the%20air%20department%20of%20the%20world's%20largest%20aircraft%20carrier%2C%20USS%20Gerald%20R.%20Ford%20(CVN%2078)%2C%20signal%20to%20launch%20an%20E-2D%20Hawkeye%20attached%20to%20the%20%26quot%3BBear%20Aces%26quot%3B%20of%20Airborne%20Command%20and%20Control%20Squadron%20(VAW)%20124%20during%20flight%20operations%20in%20the%20Adriatic%20Sea%2C%20Sept.%206%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EU.S.%20Navy%20photo%20by%20Mass%20Communication%20Specialist%202nd%20Class%20Jackson%20Adkins%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20Navy%20aircraft%20carriers%20are%20routinely%20used%20as%20power%20projection%20tools%2C%20dispatched%20to%20show%20the%20flag%2C%20show%20support%2C%20and%20stand%20as%20a%20credible%20deterrents%20in%20emergencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20introduction%20of%20the%20Ford%20gives%20the%20Navy%20greater%20capacity.%20With%20its%20inclusion%20in%20the%20fleet%20and%20deployment%2C%20the%20sea%20service%20can%20task%20its%20ten%20other%20carriers%20to%20other%20areas%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Persian%20Gulf.%20That%20gives%20the%20Navy%20an%20expanded%20presence%20and%20allows%20it%20to%20better%20meet%20demands%20from%20military%20leaders%20and%20combatant%20commanders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20USS%20Gerald%20R.%20Ford%20Carrier%20Strike%20Group%20was%20deployed%20in%20direct%20response%20to%20surprise%20terror%20attacks%20by%20Hamas%20on%20Saturday%2C%20when%20the%20group%2C%20designated%20as%20terrorists%20by%20the%20US%20State%20Department%2C%20assaulted%20Israel%20and%20killed%20over%201%2C200%20civilians%20and%20foreign%20nationals%2C%20injuring%20thousands%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Israeli%20Defense%20Force%20(IDF)%20has%20in%20turn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fisrael-devastating-airstrikes-hamas-gaza-requesting-more-bombs-weapons-2023-10%5C%22%3Elaunched%20vicious%2C%20devastating%20air%20strikes%20in%20Gaza%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20against%20the%20densely%20populated%20strip%20with%20precision-guided%20munitions%20that%20have%20destroyed%20entire%20streets%20and%2