rnia%20with%20her%20two%20one-year-olds%2C%20Exa%20and%20Tau%2C%20%26quot%3Bon%20or%20about%26quot%3B%20December%2031%2C%202022.%20In%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmusk-asked-for-relationship-grimes-kids-in-secret-lawsuit-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EMusk's%20lawsuit%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20claimed%20they%20lived%20together%20in%20Texas%20as%20recently%20as%20July%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20new%20filing%2C%20Grimes%20said%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Ftesla%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETesla%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20CEO%20is%20in%20California%20for%20work%20%26quot%3B2%20to%203%20days%20each%20week%26quot%3B%20and%20has%20only%20spent%20126%20of%20the%20last%20274%20days%20%E2%80%94%20or%2046%25%20of%20his%20time%20%E2%80%93%20in%20Austin%2C%20where%20he%20sued%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrimes%20said%20she%20was%20served%20with%20Musk's%20legal%20papers%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20and%20that%20she%20personally%20%26quot%3Bhad%20and%20continues%20to%20have%20no%20continuing%2C%20systematic%20or%20minimum%20contacts%20with%20Texas%26quot%3B%20and%20asked%20the%20Texas%20court%20to%20%26quot%3Bdismiss%20these%20proceedings.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELawyers%20for%20Musk%20didn't%20immediately%20reply%20to%20an%20email%20seeking%20comment%2C%20and%20Grimes'%20lawyers%20didn't%20immediately%20reply%20to%20a%20message%20left%20at%20their%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChrisopher%20Melcher%2C%20a%20lawyer%20at%20Walzer%20Melcher%20who%20represents%20wealthy%20clients%20in%20family%20law%20matters%2C%20said%20judges%20focus%20on%20where%20a%20child%20has%20resided%20for%20the%20past%20six%20months%20when%20deciding%20whether%20they%20can%20hear%20a%20case.%20They%20may%20also%20consider%20significant%20connections%20the%20child%20has.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTeachers%20and%20nannies%20and%20relatives%20%E2%80%94%20we%20don't%20want%20to%20inconvenience%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20they're%20in%20Texas%2C%20we%20don't%20want%20to%20have%20them%20travel%20to%20California%20for%20a%20custody%20trial.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20cases%20where%20children%20are%20%26quot%3Bnomadic%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20jetting%20from%20place%20to%20place%2C%20and%20the%20parties%20can't%20agree%20where%20the%20case%20belongs%2C%20one%20judge%20will%20sometimes%20simply%20telephone%20the%20other%20and%20hash%20out%20which%20of%20them%20will%20handle%20it%2C%20Melcher%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Musk's%20initial%20lawsuit%2C%20which%20he%20quietly%20filed%20on%20September%207%2C%20the%20billionaire%20sued%20Grimes%20to%20%26quot%3Bestablish%20the%20parent-child%20relationship%26quot%3B%20and%20access%20to%20their%20three%20children.%20He%20accused%20the%20singer%20of%20moving%20to%20California%20%26quot%3Bin%20an%20apparent%20attempt%20to%20circumvent%20jurisdiction%26quot%3B%20of%20Texas%20courts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20of%20Grimes%20wearing%20a%20red%20costume%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F647218eb085acb0018fec4a1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222661%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGrimes%20will%20split%2050%25%20of%20royalties%20with%20approved%20artists%20who%20made%20songs%20with%20her%20AI%20vocals.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20his%20part%2C%20Musk%20appears%20to%20have%20been%20working%20to%20build%20a%20home%20base%20in%20Texas.%20He%20has%20said%20he%20lives%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-house-inside-look-photo-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%2450%2C000%20home%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Texas%20that%20he%20rents%20from%20SpaceX%20and%20often%20couch%20surfs%20during%20his%20trips%20to%20California.%20It%20was%20also%20reported%20earlier%20this%20year%20that%20the%20billionaire%