value%20was%20%244.3mn.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F29113309%2FAdani_Mundra_Port_Kutch_Gujarat1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22792%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F29113309%2FAdani_Mundra_Port_Kutch_Gujarat1.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F29113309%2FAdani_Mundra_Port_Kutch_Gujarat1-300x200.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-254571%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22529%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20inflation%20in%20imported%20coal%20that%20FT%20alleges%20Adani%20has%20been%20doing%20may%20have%20sometimes%2C%20per%20the%20report%2C%20allowed%20it%20to%20make%2052%25%20profit%20margins%20in%20an%20industry%20where%20profit%20margins%20are%20otherwise%20considered%20low.%20File%20image%20of%20the%20Adani%20Mundra%20port%20in%20Gujarat%E2%80%99s%20Kutch.%20Photo%3A%20Emperor%20Genius%20at%20English%20Wikipedia%2C%20CC%20BY-SA%203.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20allowed%20for%20%E2%80%9C52%25%20profit%20margins%E2%80%9D%20as%20a%20result%20of%20over-invoicing%2C%20and%20leading%20to%20unusual%20profits.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EAn%20FT%20analysis%20supports%20longstanding%20claims%20that%20Adani%20Group%20has%20been%20inflating%20fuel%20costs%20for%20billions%20of%20dollars%20of%20coal%2C%20leading%20to%20millions%20of%20Indians%20overpaying%20for%20electricity%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FJV2GlxrBx8%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FJV2GlxrBx8%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2Fv8wlKVQY3m%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2Fv8wlKVQY3m%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Financial%20Times%20(%40FT)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FFT%2Fstatus%2F1712384879499862070%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EOctober%2012%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E%20says%20%E2%80%9Cannual%20profits%20at%20Adani%20Enterprises%20quadrupled%20over%20the%20past%20five%20years%2C%20to%20earnings%20before%20interest%2C%20tax%2C%20depreciation%20and%20amortisation%20of%20%241.2bn%20in%20the%20most%20recent%20financial%20year.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELittle-known%20middlemen%20companies%20used%20to%20import%20paid%20higher%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0FT%3C%2Fem%3E%20says%20that%20Adani%20Enterprises%2C%20the%20group%E2%80%99s%20oldest%20and%20most%20valuable%20company%2C%20generates%20the%20lion%E2%80%99s%20share%20of%20its%20sales%20and%20profits%20from%20its%20coal%20trading%20division%20called%20Integrated%20Resources%20Management%20(IRM).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20division%2C%20%E2%80%9Cboasts%20of%20its%20expertise%20in%20logistics%20and%20commodity%20trading%E2%80%9D%20based%20in%20four%20global%20offices%20and%2019%20Indian%20locations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20most%20recent%20financial%20year%2C%20which%20ended%20in%20March%2C%20IRM%20reported%20trading%2088%20million%20tonnes%20of%20coal%2C%20says%20the%20news%20report.%20Its%20results%20for%20the%20final%20quarter%20of%20that%20year%2C%20the%20first%20set%20of%20accounts%20published%20after%20Hindenburg%E2%80%99s%20report%2C%20covered%20a%20three-month%20period%20when%20the%20market%20price%20of%20coal%20had%20halved.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20notes%20%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CIRM%20thrived%2C%20delivering%20a%2024%25%20rise%20in%20earnings%20before%20tax%20and%20interest%20to%20Rs%208.3%20billion%20(%24101%20million)%2C%20on%20a%206%25%20rise%20in%20sales%20to%20Rs%20186%20billion%20(%242.3%20billion)%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20IRM%20did%20not%20make%20extraordinary%20profits.%20Three%20%E2%80%9Cmiddlemen%E2%80%9D%20companies%20it%20used%20to%20buy%20coal%20from%2C%20that%20supplied%20the%20Adani%20group%20with%20coal%2C%20appear%20to%20have%20made%20more%20substantial%20amounts%E2%80%9D.%20%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E%20identifies%20them%20as%20Hi%20Lingos%20in%20Taipei%2C%20Taurus%20Commodities%20General%20Trading%20in%20Dubai%2C%20and%20Pan%20Asia%20Tradelink%20in%20Singapore.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%2042%20million%20tonnes%20of%20coal%20supplied%20by%20its%20own%20operations%20in%20that%20time%2C%20the%20Adani%20group%20declared%20an%20average%20price%20of%20%24130%20per%20tonne.%20But%20for%20the%2031%20million%20tonnes%20of%20coal%20supplied%20by%20its%20three%20middlemen%2C%20the%20average%20price%20declared%20per%20tonne%20was%20%24155%2C%20per%20tonne.%20This%20was%20at%20a%20%E2%80%9C20%25%20premium%20worth%20almost%20%24800%20million.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E%20identifies%20Hi%20Lingos%20as%20being%20owned%20by%20Chang%20Chung-Ling%2C%20a%20Taiwanese%20businessman%20previously%20%E2%80%9Cidentified%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E%20as%20a%20potentially%20controversial%20owner%20of%20Adani%20stock.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20middleman%20company%20Taurus%2C%20it%20says%2C%20is%20run%20from%20Dubai%20and%20whose%20ownership%20it%20was%20unable%20to%20conclusively%20establish.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20company%2C%20Pan%20Asia%20Coal%20Trading%2C%20which%20%E2%80%9Cprimarily%20supplied%20Adani%20Power%20and%20did%20not%20have%20other%20Indian%20customers%20for%20coal%20in%20the%20records%20reviewed%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESenior%20industry%20traders%20%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E%20spoke%20to%2C%20%E2%80%9Cquestioned%20the%20use%20of%20little-known%20trading%20houses%2C%20as%20large%20buyers%20of%20coal%20generally%20prefer%20to%20partner%20with%20big%20trading%20houses%20that%20have%20strong%20credit%20ratings%20and%20a%20reliable%20record%20for%20commodity%20deals%20involving%20the%20exchange%20of%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E%20does%20not%20rule%20out%20the%20possibility%20of%20higher%20quality%20coal%20in%20some%20cases%20leading%20to%20a%20marginally%20higher%20price%2C%20yet%2C%20it%20notes%20that%20Adani%20also%20appears%20to%20have%20supplied%20itself%20with%20%E2%80%9Cunusually%20expensive%20coal.%20For%20the%20508%20shipments%20with%20a%20calorific%20value%20where%20Adani%20companies%20were%20listed%20as%20both%20supplier%20and%20importer%2C%20most%20%E2%80%94%2087%25%20%E2%80%94%20were%20priced%20higher%20than%20the%20closest%20Argus%20benchmark%2C%20at%20a%20median%20premium%20of%2024%25.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EArgus%20is%20an%20independent%20provider%20of%20market%20intelligence%20to%20the%20global%20energy%20and%20commodity%20markets%2C%20and%20is%20treated%20as%20a%20provider%20of%20price%20benchmarks%20globally.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F10%2F1312074_Wallpaper2.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20coal%20ministry%20is%20discouraging%20generators%20from%20going%20for%20imports%20to%20meet%20their%20fuel%20shortages.%20Credit%3A%20PTI%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22904%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-189061%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22678%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFor%2042%20million%20tonnes%20of%20coal%20supplied%20by%20its%20own%20operations%20in%20that%20time%2C%20the%20Adani%20group%20declared%20an%20average%20price%20of%20%24130%20per%20tonne.%20But%20for%20the%2031%20million%20tonnes%20of%20coal%20supplied%20by%20its%20three%20middlemen%2C%20the%20average%20price%20declared%20per%20tonne%20was%20%24155%2C%20per%20tonne.%20This%20was%20at%20a%20%E2%80%9C20%25%20premium%20worth%20almost%20%24800%20million.%E2%80%9D%20Credit%3A%20PTI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fadanis-acquisitions-india-needs-to-keep-track-costs%5C%22%3EAdani%E2%80%99s%20Acquisitions%3A%20Why%20India%20Needs%20to%20Keep%20Track%20of%20the%20Costs%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPublic%20pays%20higher%20prices%20for%20power%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20important%20implication%20of%20the%20allegedly%20overpriced%20coal%2C%20that%20the%20%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E%20investigation%20draws%20attention%20to%2C%20is%20the%20charge%20that%20these%20high%20costs%20translated%20directly%20into%20higher%20prices%20paid%20by%20consumers%2C%20especially%20in%20Gujarat%20where%20the%20opposition%20Congress%20party%20has%20already%20flagged%20the%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20August%20this%20year%2C%20opposition%20politicians%20in%20Gujarat%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Fahmedabad%2Fcongress-accuses-guvnl-of-paying-rs-3900-cr-extra-to-adani-power-govt-says-misleading-8911127%2F%5C%22%3Eaccused%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20state%20government%20of%20making%20almost%20%24500%20million%20in%20excess%20payments%20to%20Adani%20Power%20over%20five%20years%20under%20a%20power%20purchase%20agreement%20linked%20to%20the%20price%20of%20coal.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20opposition%20claimed%20a%20letter%20from%20the%20state%20power%20utility%20GUVNL%20showed%20it%20had%20paid%20the%20sums%20to%20Adani%20for%20coal%20procured%20at%20premium%20prices%2C%20and%20that%20%E2%80%9CAdani%20had%20not%20provided%20paperwork.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGUVNL%20paid%20Rs%2013%2C802%20crore%20(%242%20billion)%20as%20energy%20charges%20to%20the%20company.%20But%20if%20coal%20rates%20as%20per%20Argus%20index%20is%20taken%20into%20consideration%2C%20then%20only%20Rs%209%2C902%20crore%20(%241.5%20billion)%20should%20have%20been%20paid%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20opposition%20leader%20is%20quoted%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20then%2C%20notes%20%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20said%20that%20the%20payments%20were%20interim%20and%20%E2%80%9Csubject%20to%20adjustment%2C%E2%80%9D%20while%20Adani%20called%20the%20allegations%20%E2%80%9Cbaseless%E2%80%9D%20and%20said%20the%20contract%20had%20been%20quoted%20out%20of%20context.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20Adani%20group%20told%3Cem%3E%20FT%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20%E2%80%9Ccoal%20procurement%20on%20long-term%20supply%20basis%20in%20India%20is%20done%20through%20an%20open%2C%20transparent%2C%20global%20bidding%20process%20thereby%20eliminating%20any%20possibility%20of%20price%20manipulation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGautam%20Adani%20and%20business%20practices%20of%20his%20companies%20have%20been%20under%20scrutiny%20ever%20since%20Hindenburg%E2%80%99s%20report%20became%20public.%20You%20can%20read%20the%20Hindenburg%20report%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhindenburgresearch.com%2Fadani%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Adani%E2%80%99s%20response%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.adani.com%2F-%2Fmedia%2FProject%2FAdani%2FInvetsors%2FAdani-Response-to-Hindenburg-January-29-2023.pdf%5C%22%3Ehere.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697117605000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F08193718%2Fadani.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fadani-coal-imports-over-pricing-customers-overcharged-fuel-ft%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20detailed%20FT%20investigation%20points%20to%20Adani%E2%80%99s%20use%20of%20%E2%80%9Coffshore%20intermediaries%E2%80%9D%20to%20import%20%245%20billion%20worth%20of%20coal%20at%20prices%20that%20were%20at%20times%20more%20than%20double%20the%20market%20price.%20One%20of%20these%20firms%20is%20owned%20by%20a%20Taiwanese%20businessman%20who%20was%20named%20by%20FT%20as%20a%20hidden%20shareholder%20in%20Adani%20firms.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A79%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%