3Cspan%3ESection%2019(1)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Money%20Laundering%20Act%20(PMLA)%2C%202002%20%E2%80%93%20which%20requires%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20(ED)%20to%20inform%20the%20accused%20of%20the%20grounds%20of%20arrest%20%E2%80%93%20necessitates%20providing%20such%20grounds%20in%20a%20written%20format.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENon-compliance%20with%20this%20requirement%20vitiates%20an%20arrest%2C%20and%20entitles%20the%20accused%20to%20be%20set%20free%20unconditionally.%20Therefore%2C%20in%20the%20instant%20case%2C%20the%20court%20ordered%20the%20immediate%20release%20of%20real%20estate%20group%20M3M%E2%80%99s%20directors%20Pankaj%20Bansal%20and%20Basant%20Bansal%20in%20a%20money%20laundering%20case.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20this%20piece%2C%20I%20analyse%20the%20judgement%20and%20locate%20it%20in%20case%20law%20interpreting%20the%20PMLA%E2%80%99s%20provisions.%20I%20argue%20that%20it%20furnishes%20at%20least%20three%20principles%20under%20section%2019%2C%20non-compliance%20of%20which%20can%20be%20invoked%20as%20the%20sole%20ground%20to%20be%20released%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Efirst%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20that%20the%20accused%20has%20a%20right%20to%20receive%20the%20grounds%20of%20their%20arrest%20in%20a%20written%20format%3B%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Esecond%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20that%20a%20refusal%20to%20cooperate%20during%20interrogation%20cannot%20be%20the%20mode%20through%20which%20a%20%E2%80%9Creason%20to%20believe%E2%80%9D%20in%20one%E2%80%99s%20guilt%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20the%20threshold%20requirement%20for%20arrest%20%E2%80%93%20can%20be%20developed%3B%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ethird%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20that%20the%20ED%20cannot%20arrest%20with%20mala%20fides.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EPrinciple%201%3A%C2%A0The%20accused%20must%20receive%20written%20grounds%20of%20arrest%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20ED%20begins%20its%20investigation%20through%20the%20registration%20of%20an%20Enforcement%20Case%20Information%20Report%20(ECIR)%2C%20which%20has%20been%20described%20as%20an%20%E2%80%9Cinternal%20document%20created%20by%20the%20department%E2%80%9D%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F14485072%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EVijay%20Madanlal%20Choudhary%20vs%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20document%20has%20no%20legal%20basis%2C%20for%20no%20law%20authorises%20or%20empowers%20the%20ED%20to%20register%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20instant%20case%2C%20an%20ECIR%20concerning%20Basant%20Bansal%20was%20registered%2C%20who%20was%20arrested%20without%20receiving%20a%20copy%20of%20this%20ECIR%2C%20or%20receiving%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ewritten%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20information%20as%20to%20what%20necessitated%20his%20arrest.%20Section%2019(1)%20of%20the%20PMLA%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F581566%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EArticle%2022(1)%20of%20the%20constitution%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20require%20that%20the%20accused%20be%20informed%20of%20the%20grounds%20of%20arrest.%20Neither%20the%20constitution%20nor%20the%20section%2C%20however%2C%20provides%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20these%20grounds%20must%20be%20communicated.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20court%20held%20that%20the%20communication%20of%20the%20grounds%20of%20arrest%20must%20be%20necessarily%20done%20in%20a%20written%20manner%2C%20offering%20two%20reasons.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFirst%2C%20in%20case%20the%20grounds%20are%20read%20out%20verbally%2C%20the%20issue%20of%20whether%20such%20grounds%20were%20in%20fact%20communicated%20%E2%80%9Cboil%5Bs%5D%20down%20to%20the%20word%20of%20the%20arrested%20person%20against%20the%20word%20of%20the%20authorised%20officer%E2%80%9D.%20This%20makes%20adjudication%20of%20the%20arrest%E2%80%99s%20validity%20a%20difficult%20task.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20instant%20case%2C%20the%20ED%20claimed%20to%20have%20read%20out%20the%20grounds%20of%20arrest%20in%20Hindi%20in%20front%20of%20witnesses%2C%20while%20Bansal%20claimed%20that%20no%20such%20attempt%20was%20made.%20This%20state%20of%20affairs%2C%20the%20court%20noted%2C%20is%20%E2%80%9Cneither%20here%20nor%20there%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESecond%2C%20it%20noted%20that%20the%20PMLA%E2%80%99s%20bail%20regime%20is%20such%20that%20it%20prevents%20one%E2%80%99s%20release%20as%20long%20as%20a%20reasonable%20case%20is%20present%2C%20which%20%E2%80%93%20in%20order%20to%20be%20argued%20by%20the%20accused%20%E2%80%93%20necessitates%20their%20own%20knowledge%20of%20the%20case%20against%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20this%20basis%2C%20it%20held%20that%20whenever%20the%20ED%20makes%20an%20arrest%2C%20it%20must%20necessarily%20furnish%20its%20grounds%20in%20a%20written%20format.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20court%20was%20also%20confronted%20with%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EVM%20Choudhary%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20which%20held%20the%20ECIR%E2%80%99s%20supply%20non-mandatory%20as%20long%20as%20the%20accused%20was%20informed%20of%20the%20grounds%20of%20their%20arrest%20one%20way%20or%20another.%20In%20the%20instant%20case%2C%20the%20court%20held%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EVM%20Choudhary%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20left%20open%20the%20question%20of%20how%20the%20accused%20would%20be%20informed%20of%20the%20grounds%20of%20arrest%20short%20of%20the%20ECIR%E2%80%99s%20supply%2C%20an%20area%20of%20law%20that%20could%20be%20developed%20separately.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ftracking-the-ed-case-by-case-puzzling-questions-emerge-in-its-handling-of-opposition-leaders%5C%22%3ETracking%20the%20ED%20Case%20by%20Case%2C%20Puzzling%20Questions%20Emerge%20in%20Its%20Handling%20of%20Opposition%20Leaders%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EPrinciple%202%3A%20Non-cooperation%20during%20interrogation%20cannot%20be%20a%20ground%20for%20arrest%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20the%20ED%20summons%20an%20accused%20using%20its%20powers%20under%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1395568%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESection%2050%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0of%20the%20PMLA%2C%20it%20dons%20a%20judicial%20character%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Efor%20Section%2050(4)%20converts%20all%20summons%20proceedings%20into%20judicial%20proceedings%20within%20the%20meaning%20of%20sections%20193%20and%20228%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC)%2C%201860.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20person%20being%20interrogated%20must%20furnish%20truthful%20answers%20to%20all%20questions%20asked.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ENon-compliance%20with%20directions%20to%20attend%20or%20produce%20evidence%20is%20punishable%20with%20fines%20under%20Section%2063(2).%20False%20answers%20may%20invite%20the%20penalty%20under%20Section%20193%20of%20the%20IPC%2C%20carrying%20a%20term%20of%20up%20to%20seven%20years%20in%20prison.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20setup%20was%20challenged%20based%20on%20its%20incompatibility%20with%20the%20guarantee%20against%20self-incrimination%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EVM%20Choudhary%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20court%20upheld%20it%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20the%20person%20undergoing%20questioning%20is%20not%20formally%20an%20%E2%80%9Caccused%E2%80%9D%20at%20the%20summons%20stage%2C%20making%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F366712%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EArticle%2020(3)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20the%20constitution%20inapplicable.%20In%20that%20case%2C%20the%20court%20also%20noted%20that%20since%20interrogation%20during%20summons%20assumes%20a%20judicial%20character%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F494844%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESection%2025%20of%20the%20Evidence%20Act%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0which%20makes%20confessions%20to%20the%20police%20inadmissible%E2%80%93%C2%A0would%20not%20apply.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20present%20case%2C%20the%20ED%20interrogated%20Pankaj%20Bansal%20at%20the%20summons%20stage%2C%20who%20%E2%80%93%20according%20to%20the%20ED%20%E2%80%93%20furnished%20%E2%80%9Cevasive%E2%80%9D%20answers.%20His%20uncooperative%20behaviour%2C%20the%20ED%20admitted%2C%20caused%20his%20arrest.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20court%20held%20that%20providing%20evasive%20answers%20or%20exhibiting%20generally%20uncooperative%20behaviour%20during%20summons%20cannot%20be%20grounds%20for%20arrest.%20It%20noted%20that%20the%20extraction%20of%20confessions%20cannot%20be%20the%20sole%20pursuit%20of%20the%20summons%20stage%2C%20and%20the%20accused%E2%80%99s%20refusal%20to%20incriminate%20themselves%20does%20not%20constitute%20uncooperative%20behaviour.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20observation%20carries%20a%20notable%20dissonance%20with%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EVM%20Choudhary%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20for%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20conclusion%20that%20evasiveness%20cannot%20constitute%20a%20ground%20for%20arrest%20lies%20%E2%80%93%20ultimately%20%E2%80%93%20in%20the%20applicability%20of%20the%20guarantee%20against%20self-incrimination%20during%20summons.%20This%20is%20because%20the%20court%20cites%20case-law%20to%20the%20effect%20that%20interrogation%2C%20overall%2C%20must%20not%20be%20discriminatory%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20any%20event%2C%20it%20is%20not%20open%20to%20the%20ED%20to%20expect%20an%20admission%20of%20guilt%20from%20the%20person%20summoned%20for%20interrogation%20and%20assert%20that%20anything%20short%20of%20such%20admission%20would%20be%20an%20%E2%80%98evasive%20reply%E2%80%99.%20In%20%3C%2Fem%3ESantosh%20vs.%20State%20of%20Maharashtra%3Cem%3E%2C%20this%20Court%20noted%20that%20custodial%20interrogation%20is%20not%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20%E2%80%98confession%E2%80%99%20as%20the%20right%20against%20self-incrimination%20is%20provided%20by%20Article%2020(3)%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20It%20was%20held%20that%20merely%20because%20an%20accused%20did%20not%20confess%2C%20it%20cannot%20be%20said%20that%20he%20was%20not%20co-operating%20with%20the%20investigation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F119468908%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESantosh%20vs%20State%20of%20Maharashtra%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20a%20case%20where%20the%20state%20opposed%20an%20accused%E2%80%99s%20bail%20due%20to%20their%20refusal%20to%20confess%2C%20the%20court%20noted%20that%20a%20conceptualisation%20of%20undertrial%20interrogation%20such%20that%20it%20was%20wholly%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20extracting%20confessions%20was%20an%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eunconstitutional%20expectation%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20This%20was%20because%20Article%2020(3)%20possessed%20an%20%E2%80%9Cexalted%20status%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20constitutional%20scheme.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20court%E2%80%99s%20holding%20that%20the%20ED%20cannot%20expect%20%E2%80%9Cadmissions%20of%20guilt%E2%80%9D%20during%20the%20summons%20stage%20means%20that%20the%20accused%20is%20not%20bound%20to%20incriminate.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20this%20means%20that%20the%20accused%E2%80%99s%20right%20against%20self-incrimination%20may%20apply%20even%20during%20the%20summons%20stage%20Under%20Section%2050.%20This%20proposition%20conflicts%20with%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EVM%20Choudhary%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20which%20may%20be%20settled%20by%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-bihar-caste-survey-refuses-to-restrain-bihar-govt-from-acting-on-caste-survey-data-239479%3Finfinitescroll%3D1%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethree-judge%20bench%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20reviewing%20that%20case%20soon.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F07%2F21161633%2F2022_7img21_Jul_2022_PTI07_21_2022_000078B.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F07%2F21161633%2F2022_7img21_Jul_2022_PTI07_21_2022_000078B.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F07%2F21161633%2F2022_7img21_Jul_2022_PTI07_21_2022_000078B-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F07%2F21161633%2F2022_7img21_Jul_2022_PTI07_21_2022_000078B-1024x682.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-609187%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22799%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECongress%20MPs%20holding%20banners%20and%20placards%20stage%20a%20protest%20march%20at%20Parliament%20House%20against%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate.%20Photo%3A%20PTI%2FKamal%20Kishore%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EPrinciple%203%3A%C2%A0The%20ED%20cannot%20arrest%20with%20mala%20fides%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPankaj%20and%20Basant%20Bansal%2C%20the%20two%20accused%20in%20the%20present%20case%2C%20obtained%20anticipatory%20bail%20from%20the%20Delhi%20high%20court%20when%20they%20obtained%20information%20about%20the%20filing%20of%20an%20ECIR%20against%20a%20third%20person%20connected%20with%20their%20company.%20The%20ED%2C%20however%2C%20registered%20a%20second%20ECIR%20against%20both%20accused%20within%20four%20days%20of%20their%20anticipatory%20bail%2C%20and%20arrested%20them%20within%2024%20hours%20thereafter.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20court%20labelled%20the%20arrests%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccolourable%20exercise%20of%20power%E2%80%9D%2C%20noting%20that%20the%20ED%E2%80%99s%20actions%20showed%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccomplete%20and%20utter%20lack%20of%20bonafides%E2%80%9D.%20Since%20the%20threshold%20of%20arrest%20under%20Section%2019%20is%20that%20the%20ED%2C%20based%20on%20the%20material%20in%20its%20possession%2C%20believes%20in%20the%20accused%E2%80%99s%20guilt%2C%20the%20court%20noted%20that%20a%20period%20of%2024%20hours%20from%20an%20ECIR%E2%80%99s%20registration%20would%20be%20inadequate%20for%20this%20belief%E2%80%99s%20formation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20court%20also%20held%20that%20the%20ED%E2%80%99s%20suppression%20of%20materials%20at%20an%20anticipatory%20bail%20hearing%2C%20which%20could%20be%20used%20for%20re-arrest%2C%20indicated%20an%20abuse%20of%20power%20and%20vitiated%20the%20arrest.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EShifting%20interpretive%20lenses%20%E2%80%93%20institutional%20omnipotence%20or%20procedural%20rights%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20prevailing%20trend%20in%20case%20law%20interpreting%20the%20PMLA%20has%20been%20to%20bolster%20the%20ED%E2%80%99s%20investigative%20powers%2C%20based%20on%20an%20abstract%20fear%20of%20the%20money-laundering%20offence.%20In%20the%20quest%20to%20create%20an%20omnipotent%20entity%20to%20eradicate%20money%20laundering%2C%20courts%20have%20painted%20it%20with%20immense%20illegibility%2C%20holding%20that%20the%20offence%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheproofofguilt.blogspot.com%2F2022%2F07%2Fold-wine-in-new-bottles-judgment-in.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esui%20generis%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%20character%20necessitates%20an%20institution%20that%20defies%20classification.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EVM%20Choudhary%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20court%20held%20that%20the%20ED%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20consist%20of%20the%20police%2C%20and%20confessions%20made%20to%20(or%20extracted%20by)%20its%20officers%20would%20be%20admissible%20in%20evidence.%20Recently%2C%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2023%2F28176%2F28176_2023_7_1501_45841_Judgement_07-Aug-2023.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESenthil%20Balaji%20vs%20State%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20court%20held%20that%20despite%20the%20ED%E2%80%99s%20officials%20not%20being%20the%20%E2%80%9Cpolice%E2%80%9D%2C%20they%20are%20still%20entitled%20to%20take%20an%20accused%20into%20%E2%80%9Cpolice%20custody%E2%80%9D%20in%20order%20to%20undertake%20even%20more%20interrogation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBalaji%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20it%20was%20also%20held%20that%20Section%2041-A%20of%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%2C%20which%20provides%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnotice%20of%20appearance%E2%80%9D%20as%20a%20lesser%20rights-restrictive%20alternative%20to%20police%20custody%2C%20would%20be%20inapplicable%20to%20the%20PMLA%20in%20toto.%20The%20following%20reasoning%20was%20offered%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CFollowing%20Section%2041A%20of%20the%20CrPC%2C%201973%20for%20an%20arrest%20under%20the%20PMLA%2C%202002%20would%20only%20defeat%20and%20destroy%20the%20very%20inquiry%2Finvestigation%20under%20the%20PMLA%2C%202002.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ETill%20summons%20are%20issued%20to%20a%20person%2C%20he%20is%20not%20expected%20to%20be%20in%20the%20know-how.%20Any%20prior%20intimation%2C%20other%20than%20what%20is%20mandated%20under%20the%20PMLA%2C%201973%20might%20seriously%20impair%20the%20ongoing%20investigation%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20interpretive%20lens%20of%20strengthening%20the%20ED%20was%20dominant%20in%20case%20law.%20Consistency%20of%20propositions%2C%20such%20as%20the%20decision%20over%20whether%20the%20ED%20consisted%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cpolice%E2%80%9D%2C%20was%20open%20to%20compromises.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBansal%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20marks%20a%20degree%20of%20dissent%20from%20this%20interpretive%20lens%20of%20offering%20the%20ED%20unconditional%20strength%2C%20as%20well%20as%20from%20legal%20propositions%20laid%20down%20in%20such%20case%20law.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20court%20veers%20towards%20applying%20the%20guarantee%20against%20self-incrimination%20to%20the%20ED%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cjudicial%E2%80%9D%20interrogation%2C%20and%20makes%20mandatory%20the%20supply%20of%20written%20grounds%20of%20arrest.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25222448%2FSupreme-Court-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25222448%2FSupreme-Court-1.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25222448%2FSupreme-Court-1-300x174.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25222448%2FSupreme-Court-1-1024x595.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-665108%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22697%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India.%20Photo%3A%20The%20Wire%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENew%20procedural%20challenges%20to%20arrest%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20significance%20of%20the%20judgment%2C%20however%2C%20lies%20in%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20introduces%20a%20new%20set%20of%20legal%20challenges%20capable%20of%20immediate%20fructification%20by%20those%20arrested%20under%20the%20PMLA.%20All%20PMLA%20undertrials%2C%20therefore%2C%20can%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Enow%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20argue%20for%20the%20invalidity%20of%20their%20arrests%20based%20on%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBansal%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20three%20principles%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Efirst%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20non-supply%20of%20written%20grounds%3B%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Esecond%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20absence%20of%20grounds%20other%20than%20mere%20%E2%80%9Cevasiveness%E2%80%9D%3B%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ethird%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20presence%20of%20mala%20fides.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20because%20of%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20observation%20that%20the%20passage%20of%20an%20initial%20order%20of%20remand%20is%20immaterial%20to%20the%20analysis%20of%20the%20arrest%E2%80%99s%20overall%20validity%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%5BW%5De%20may%20also%20make%20it%20clear%20that%20the%20mere%20passing%20of%20an%20order%20of%20remand%20would%20not%20be%20sufficient%20in%20itself%20to%20validate%20the%20appellants%E2%80%99%20arrests%2C%20if%20such%20arrests%20are%20not%20in%20conformity%20with%20the%20requirements%20of%20Section%2019%20of%20the%20Act%20of%202002.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20judgement%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBansal%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20therefore%2C%20is%20a%20valuable%20step%20towards%20making%20basic%20procedural%20rights%20applicable%20to%20the%20ED.%20Compliance%20with%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBansal%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20three%20principles%20may%20afford%20greater%20institutional%20accountability%20and%20may%20offer%20some%20relief%20to%20PMLA%20undertrials%20by%20equipping%20them%20to%20challenge%20the%20validity%20of%20their%20arrests.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKartik%20Kalra%20is%20a%20student%20at%20the%20National%20Law%20School%20of%20India%20University%2C%20Bengaluru.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697106646000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F29180215%2FThe-Wire-1.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fpankaj-bansal-verdict-valuable-step-basic-procedural-rights-applicable-ed%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20prevailing%20trend%20in%20case%20law%20interpreting%20the%20PMLA%20has%20been%20to%20bolster%20the%20ED%E2%80%99s%20investigative%20powers%2C%20based%20on%20an%20abstract%20fear%20of%20money%20laundering.%20The%20top%20court%20setting%20real%20estate%20baron%20Pankaj%20Bansal%20free%20marks%20a%20degree%20of%20departure.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fpankaj-bansal-verdict-valuable-step-basic-procedural-rights-applicable-ed%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22France%20Hopes%20to%20Best%20US%20in%20New%20India%20Fighter%20Race%2C%20Betting%20on%20Existing%20Rafale%20Sales%2C%20Tech%20Flexibility%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12153245%2FF8KgdHwaEAAXScv.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChandigarh%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20overlapping%20visits%20of%20Indian%20defence%20minister%20Rajnath%20Singh%20to%20Paris%20and%20that%20of%20France%E2%80%99s%20Dassault%20Aviation%20head%20Eric%20Trappier%20to%20New%20Delhi%20this%20week%20is%20an%C2%A0%20indication%20of%20the%20augmented%20level%20of%20bilateral%20military%20commerce%2C%20especially%20of%20combat%20aircraft%2C%20between%20the%20two%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20October%2010-12%20trip%20to%20Italy%20and%20France%20focused%2C%20in%20the%20latter%20instance%2C%20on%20possible%20collaborations%20with%20its%20military-industrial%20complex%20to%20further%20India%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Atmanirbharta%E2%80%99%20initiative%20to%20reduce%20materiel%20imports%2C%20Trappier%E2%80%99s%20Delhi%20visit%2C%20between%20October%209-10%2C%20was%20focused%20on%20supplying%20the%20Indian%20Navy%2026%20Rafale-M%20(Maritime)%20fighters%20for%20embarkation%20on%20%3Cem%3EINS%20Vikrant%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20its%20newly%20commissioned%20aircraft%20carrier.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccompanied%20by%20senior%20Dassault%20executive%20Richard%20Lavaud%2C%20Trappier%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20held%20talks%20with%20top%20defence%20and%20foreign%20ministry%20officials%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20Indian%20Air%20Force%20(IAF)%20and%20Indian%20Navy%20chiefs%20of%20staff%2C%20in%20which%20the%20delivery%20of%2022%20twin-engine%2C%20canard%20delta-wing%20Rafale-M%20fighters%20and%20four%20dual-seat%20trainers%20featured%20prominently.%20However%2C%20no%20official%20statement%20on%20these%20meetings%20have%2C%20so%20far%2C%20been%20provided.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12153612%2FF8KgdH2aUAAcLfl.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12153612%2FF8KgdH2aUAAcLfl.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12153612%2FF8KgdH2aUAAcLfl-300x165.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12153612%2FF8KgdH2aUAAcLfl-1024x561.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-679728%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22658%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERajnath%20Singh%20with%20the%20CEOs%20of%20the%20top%20French%20defence%20companies%20including%20Eric%20Trappier%2C%20CEO%20of%20Dassault%2C%20Pierre%20Eric%20Pommellet%2C%20CEO%20of%20Naval%20Group%2C%20Guillaume%20Faury%2C%20CEO%20of%20Airbus%2C%20and%20Olivier%20Andries%2C%20CEO%20of%20Safran%20Group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EDassault%20is%20also%20a%20frontrunner%20for%20the%20IAF%E2%80%99s%20long-pending%20requirement%20for%20114%20multi-role%20fighter%20aircraft%20(MRFA)%20with%20its%20Rafale.%20In%202016%2C%20India%20bought%2036%20via%20an%20inter-governmental%20agreement%20or%20IGA%20for%20around%20%249%20billion%20and%20divided%20them%20between%20two%20squadrons%20at%20Ambala%20and%20Hasimara%20Air%20Force%20Stations.%20Further%20strengthening%20Dassault%E2%80%99s%20credentials%20for%20the%20MRFA%20buy%20was%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20had%20already%20established%20a%20Rafale%20flight%20training%20and%20maintenance%2C%20repair%20and%20overhaul%20facility%20at%20Ambala%2C%20which%20would%20go%20a%20long%20way%20towards%20reducing%20overall%20costs%20for%20all%20further%20similar%20fighter%20buys.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20more%20importantly%2C%20acquiring%20tried%20and%20tested%20Rafales%20would%20also%20hasten%20fighter%20inductions%20by%20dispensing%20with%20extended%20trials%2C%20to%20speedily%20boost%20the%20IAFs%20declining%20fighter%20squadrons%2C%20which%20had%20depreciated%20to%2029-30%2C%20from%20a%20sanctioned%20strength%20of%2042%20squadrons.%20Additionally%2C%20industry%20officials%20said%20acquiring%20supplementary%20Rafales%20would%20also%20streamline%20the%20IAFs%20diverse%20fighter%20catalogue%2C%20which%20presently%20features%20seven%20different%20aircraft%20types%2C%20sustaining%20all%20of%20which%20was%20not%20only%20an%20enduring%20logistical%20nightmare%2C%20but%20also%20a%20hugely%20expensive%20affair%20for%20the%20financially%20overstretched%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20IAF%20has%20had%20a%20long-established%20association%20with%20Dassault%2C%20which%20began%20in%201953%20with%20the%20arrival%20at%20Ambala%20of%20the%20first%20of%20some%20104%20of%20its%20MD%20450%20Ouragan%20fighter-bombers.%20Renamed%20Toofani%20%E2%80%93%20a%20direct%20translation%20from%20the%20aircraft%E2%80%99s%20French%20name%2C%20meaning%20Hurricane%20and%20also%20because%20Ouragan%20was%20difficult%20for%20IAF%20technicians%20and%20other%20personnel%20to%20pronounce%20%E2%80%93%20these%20fighters%20remained%20in%20service%20till%20the%20mid-1960%E2%80%99s%20and%20continued%20thereafter%20as%20advanced%20trainers%20and%20as%20target%20tugs.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fdefence-ties-serve-as-the-basic-pillar-of-india-france-bilateral-relations-modi%5C%22%3EIndia%2C%20France%20Announce%20Deals%20for%20Submarines%20and%20Jet%20Engines%2C%20but%20Silent%20on%20Rafale%20Naval%20Jets%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Toofanis%20%E2%80%93%20of%20which%2033%20were%20acquired%20in%20refurbished%20condition%20%E2%80%93%20were%20replaced%201957%20onwards%20by%20an%20equal%20number%20of%20Dassault%20Mystere%20IVA%E2%80%99s%20which%20were%20the%20first%20transonic%20aircraft%2C%20powered%20by%20Rolls-Royce%20Tay%20turbojets%2C%20to%20be%20commissioned%20into%20the%20French%20Air%20Force%20in%20the%20early%201950s.%20The%20IAF%20employed%20the%20Mystere%E2%80%99s%20extensively%20in%20the%201965%20war%20with%20Pakistan%20and%20in%20a%20limited%20role%20during%20the%20subsequent%201971%20operations%2C%20before%20eventually%20retiring%20them%20in%201973.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20hiatus%20of%20a%20little%20over%20a%20decade%2C%20the%20IAF%20began%20inducting%20some%2050-odd%20Mirage-2000Hs%20(Hindustan%E2%80%99s)%20in%201986%2C%20which%20are%20presently%20being%20upgraded%20by%20Hindustan%20Aeronautics%20Limited%20(HAL)%20in%20Bangalore%20via%20a%20transfer%20of%20technology%20from%20Dassault%20under%20a%20%242.5%20billion%20contract%20signed%20in%202011.%20This%20retrofit%20was%20scheduled%20for%20completion%20by%20end-2021%2C%20but%20has%20been%20delayed%20and%20awaits%20conclusion.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Mirage-2000Hs%20were%2C%20in%20turn%20followed%20up%20with%2036%20Rafales%2C%20including%20six%20twin-seat%20trainers%2C%20all%20of%20which%20had%20been%20commissioned%20into%20service%20by%20late%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F01%2F11174740%2FDassault_Rafale_M_of_Flottille_17F_lands_aboard_USS_George_H.W._Bush_CVN-77_in_the_Atlantic_Ocean_on_10_May_2018_180510-N-UV609-0540.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F01%2F11174740%2FDassault_Rafale_M_of_Flottille_17F_lands_aboard_USS_George_H.W._Bush_CVN-77_in_the_Atlantic_Ocean_on_10_May_2018_180510-N-UV609-0540.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F01%2F11174740%2FDassault_Rafale_M_of_Flottille_17F_lands_aboard_USS_George_H.W._Bush_CVN-77_in_the_Atlantic_Ocean_on_10_May_2018_180510-N-UV609-0540-300x150.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F01%2F11174740%2FDassault_Rafale_M_of_Flottille_17F_lands_aboard_USS_George_H.W._Bush_CVN-77_in_the_Atlantic_Ocean_on_10_May_2018_180510-N-UV609-0540-1024x513.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F01%2F11174740%2FDassault_Rafale_M_of_Flottille_17F_lands_aboard_USS_George_H.W._Bush_CVN-77_in_the_Atlantic_Ocean_on_10_May_2018_180510-N-UV609-0540-800x400.jpg%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-575273%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22601%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentative%20image%20of%20a%20Rafale%20Marine%20aircraft.%20Photo%3A%20By%20US%20Navy%2FWikimedia%20Commons%2C%20Public%20Domain%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndustry%20officials%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20indicated%20that%20Trappier%20was%20eyeing%20the%20IAFs%20MRFA%20procurement%20that%20envisages%20importing%20a%20squadron%20of%2018%20shortlisted%20fighters%20in%20flyaway%20condition%20from%20amongst%20seven%20models%20on%20offer%20from%20overseas%20original%20equipment%20manufacturers%20(OEMs)%2C%20in%20response%20to%20the%20forces%20April%202018%20request%20for%20information.%20The%20remaining%2096%20platforms%20would%20be%20built%20indigenously%2C%20via%20a%20collaborative%20venture%20between%20the%20qualified%20OEM%20and%20a%20domestic%20strategic%20partner%20from%20either%20the%20private%20or%20public%20sector%2C%20with%20progressively%20enhanced%20levels%20of%20indigenisation%2C%20in%20the%20deal%2C%20estimated%20at%20around%20%2425%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20MRFA%20tender%20is%20expected%20imminently%2C%20industry%20sources%20said%2C%20and%20senior%20IAF%20officers%20estimate%20that%20these%20numbers%20could%20increase%20to%20around%20200%20units%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20possible%20export%20options%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20platforms%20cost%20amortisation.%20Recent%20media%20reports%2C%20quoting%20official%20sources%2C%20revealed%20that%20even%20though%20the%20IAF%20planned%20on%20inducting%20some%20180%20variants%20of%20the%20indigenously%20developed%20Tejas%20Light%20Combat%20Aircraft%20to%20replace%20legacy%20fighters%20like%20the%20ground%20attack%20MiG-21s%20and%20SEPECAT%20Jaguars%2C%20the%20MRFA%20acquisition%20remained%20%E2%80%98on%20stream%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20six%20other%20OEMs%2C%20besides%20Dassault%2C%20who%20had%20responded%20to%20the%20IAF%E2%80%99s%20request%20for%20information%20include%20Eurofighter%20(Typhoon)%2C%20Sweden%E2%80%99s%20Saab%20(Gripen-E)%2C%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20United%20Aircraft%20Corporation%20and%20Sukhoi%20Corporation%20(MiG-35%20%E2%80%98Fulcrum-F%E2%80%99%20and%20Su-35%E2%80%99%20Flanker-E%E2%80%99)%20and%20the%20US%E2%80%99s%20%C2%A0Boeing%20and%20Lockheed%20Martin%20(F%2FA-18%20and%20F-15EX%20and%20the%20upgraded%20F-21).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20view%20of%20the%20ongoing%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20evaluating%20the%20two%20Russian%20fighter%20types%20for%20eventual%20IAF%20acquisition%20was%2C%20justifiably%20irrational%2C%20considering%20the%20grave%20spares%20and%20components%20crisis%20the%20force%20is%20facing%20with%20regard%20to%20its%20fleet%20of%20some%20260%20multi-role%20Sukhoi-30%20MKI%E2%80%99s%20and%2050-odd%20upgraded%20MiG-29M%20fighter-bombers.%20At%20his%20annual%20press%20conference%20last%20week%20Air%20Chief%20Marshal%20V.R.%20Chaudhuri%20declared%20that%20the%20IAF%20planned%20on%20locally%20upgrading%2084%20of%20its%20260-odd%20Su-30MKI%E2%80%99s%20to%20%E2%80%98Super%20Sukhoi%E2%80%99%20status%20for%20Rs%2060%2C000%20crore%2C%20a%20venture%20that%20had%20earlier%20focused%20heavily%20on%20direct%20Russian%20involvement.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlternately%2C%20shortlisting%20the%20Typhoon%20would%20only%20mean%20adding%20to%20the%20IAFs%20massive%20continuing%20logistic%20challenges%2C%20whilst%20the%20US%E2%80%99s%20F-18%20and%20the%20F-16%20%E2%80%93%20a%20precursor%20to%20the%20F-21%2C-had%20both%20been%20rejected%20by%20the%20IAF%20on%20multiple%20capability%20counts%20during%20trials%20conducted%202010%20onwards%20for%20the%20binned%20Medium%20Multi-Role%20Combat%20Aircraft%20contract%20floated%20in%202007.%20Saab%E2%80%99s%20Gripen-E%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20was%20a%20single-engine%20platform%2C%20and%20though%20the%20MRFA%20request%20for%20information%20had%20not%20specified%20any%20preference%20for%20single%20or%20dual%20power%20packs%2C%20the%20IAFs%20intrinsic%20preference%20for%20the%20latter%20remains%20unstated.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Findian-navy-rafale-deal-paris-bastille-day-modi%5C%22%3EIs%20There%20a%20Link%20Between%20Indian%20Navy%E2%80%99s%20Rafale-M%20Deal%20and%20the%20Paris%20Bastille%20Day%20Invite%20to%20Modi%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHence%2C%20by%20a%20process%20of%20elimination%2C%20the%20Rafale%20was%20more%20than%20favourably%20placed%20in%20the%20MRFA%20sweepstakes%2C%20due%20not%20only%20to%20its%20operational%20superiority%20over%20its%20competitors%20as%20acknowledged%20by%20the%20IAF%20%E2%80%93%20and%20now%20by%20the%20IN%20but%20also%20the%20host%20of%20multiple%20ancillary%20factors%20enumerated%20earlier.%20Besides%2C%20with%2026%20Rafale-M%20under%20purchase%2C%20that%20would%20make%20it%20an%20aggregate%20of%2062%20French%20fighters%20in%20service%20with%20the%20Indian%20military.%20Adding%20to%20these%20numbers%2C%20a%20cross-section%20of%20veterans%20said%2C%20made%20%E2%80%98eminent%E2%80%99%20commercial%2C%20logistical%20and%20operational%20sense.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20there%20was%20also%20the%20abandoned%20contractual%20template%20for%20the%20terminated%20Medium%20Multi-Role%20Combat%20Aircraft%20tender%20which%2C%20industry%20officials%20said%2C%20could%20easily%20be%20%E2%80%98tweaked%E2%80%99%20to%20suit%20an%20analogous%20MRFA%20purchase%20by%20resolving%20earlier%20glitches%20that%20would%20significantly%20compress%20negotiations.%20These%20earlier%20anomalies%20had%20centred%20on%20insistence%20by%20the%20MoD%20that%20Dassault%2C%20which%20was%20eventually%20shortlisted%2C%20shoulder%20eventual%20quality%20control%20responsibility%20for%20the%20108%20Rafales%20licence-built%20by%20HAL.%20This%20unwarranted%20conditionality%20had%20allegedly%20emerged%20as%20the%20deal-breaker%20for%20the%20Medium%20Multi-Role%20Combat%20Aircraft%20deal%20led%20to%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defence%20procuring%20just%2036%20Rafales%20in%20fly-away%20condition%2C%20according%20to%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20account.%20Of%20course%2C%20what%20was%20left%20unexplained%20was%20why%2C%20on%20the%20eve%20of%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20visit%20to%20France%20in%202015%20(when%20the%20126%20jet%20co-production%20deal%20was%20scrapped%20in%20favour%20of%20buying%2036%20outright)%2C%20both%20Dassault%20and%20HAL%20had%20said%20they%20had%20ironed%20out%20their%20differences.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20Indian%20diplomats%2C%20security%20officials%20and%20analysts%20say%C2%A0it%20is%20less%20%E2%80%98arduous%E2%80%99%20conducting%20materiel%20commerce%20with%20Paris%20than%20with%20Washington%2C%20as%20the%20former%20is%20more%20flexible%20and%20pragmatic%20than%20the%20latter%2C%20especially%20with%20regard%20to%20transferring%20hi-tech%20military%20knowhow%20and%20passing%20on%20source-codes%20that%20manage%20fighter%20weapon%20and%20flight%20control%20systems.%20The%20US%2C%20for%20its%20part%2C%20remains%C2%A0constrained%C2%A0by%20rigid%20export%20regulations%20in%20this%20regard%20and%20hidebound%20by%20personal%20political%20and%20diplomatic%20considerations%20over%20platform%20deployments.%20France%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20is%20more%20%E2%80%98relaxed%E2%80%99%20on%20all%20these%20counts%2C%20displaying%20a%20Gallic%20%3Cem%3Esavoir%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3Efaire%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20strategically%20suits%20India%2C%20even%20if%20its%20equipment%20ends%20up%20being%20relatively%20more%20expensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697105702000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12153245%2FF8KgdHwaEAAXScv.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Ffrance-us-fighter-jet-dassault-tech-rafale%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Today%2C%20Indian%20diplomats%2C%20security%20officials%20and%20analysts%20say%C2%A0it%20is%20less%20%E2%80%98arduous%E2%80%99%20conducting%20materiel%20commerce%20with%20Paris%20than%20with%20Washington.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Ffrance-us-fighter-jet-dassault-tech-rafale%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sheikh%20Hasina%20and%20the%20Question%20of%20Nepotism%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12140159%2FF6jsHPjacAA7LFS.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EBangladesh%20and%20Nepal%20are%20the%20closest%20partners%20among%20the%20countries%20of%20South%20Asia%2C%20with%20similar%20worldview%20and%20positions%20on%20most%20matters%2C%20including%20agreement%20on%20the%20SAARC%20philosophy%20of%20regionalism%20for%20progress.%20Dhaka%20and%20Kathmandu%20are%20the%20most%20proximate%20capitals%20distance-wise%2C%20and%20one%20would%20expect%20progressively%20closer%20contact%20between%20the%20two%20societies%2C%20even%20as%20plans%20for%20Nepali%20hydropower%20export%20to%20Bangladesh%20inches%20forward%20with%20the%20concurrence%20of%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20there%20is%20a%20kind%20of%20rupture%20underway%20between%20the%20two%20societies%2C%20from%20an%20unexpected%20source%20%E2%80%93%20the%20candidacy%20to%20the%20post%20of%20regional%20director%20of%20the%20World%20Health%20Organisation%E2%80%99s%20office%20that%20deals%20with%20much%20of%20South%20and%20Southeast%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20countries%20are%20in%20the%20fray%20for%20a%20position%20held%20till%20now%20by%20Indian%20national%20Dr%20Poonam%20Khetrapal%20Singh.%20The%20regional%20director%20is%20elected%20by%2011%20countries%20of%20the%20region%20comprising%20Bhutan%2C%20Bangladesh%2C%20India%2C%20Indonesia%2C%20Maldives%2C%20Myanmar%2C%20Nepal%2C%20North%20Korea%2C%20Sri%20Lanka%2C%20Thailand%20and%20Timor%20Leste.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENepal%20proposes%20Dr%20Shambhu%20Acharya%2C%20a%20public%20health%20expert%20with%20decades%20of%20experience%20in%20senior%20positions%20in%20the%20WHO%20right%20through%20the%20Covid%20crisis%2C%20a%20director%20working%20closely%20with%20Director-General%20Tedros%20Ghebreyesus.%20Bangladesh%20proposes%20Saima%20Wazed%20Hossain%20%E2%80%98Putul%E2%80%99%2C%20daughter%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Sheikh%20Hasina%2C%20who%20has%20been%20a%20school%20psychologist%20in%20the%20United%20States%20and%20leads%20a%20foundation%20on%20autism%20in%20Dhaka.%20As%20a%20citizen%20of%20Canada%20and%20Bangladesh%2C%20Wazed%20shuttles%20between%20North%20America%20and%20Bangladesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20importance%20of%20what%20is%20formally%20known%20as%20the%20WHO-SEARO%20regional%20office%2C%20with%20responsibility%20to%20provide%20public%20health%20oversight%20to%20more%20than%20two%20billion%20people%2C%20it%20is%20shocking%20to%20see%20Bangladesh%E2%80%99s%20prime%20minister%20seek%20to%20foist%20a%20family%20member%20with%20poor%20qualifications%20upon%20the%20organisation.%20The%20senior%20management%20of%20WHO%2C%20a%20specialised%20agency%20of%20the%20United%20Nations%20system%2C%20is%20said%20to%20be%20taken%20aback%20and%20concerned%20over%20the%20institutional%20implications%20of%20such%20personalised%20politicisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHasina%20has%20been%20energetically%20nepotistic%2C%20using%20all%20diplomatic%20tools%20at%20hand%20even%20as%20her%20proven%20autocratic%20ways%20force%20Dhaka%20intellectuals%20who%20think%20otherwise%20to%20maintain%20silence.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20Prime%20Minister%20Pushpa%20Kamal%20Dahal%20(%E2%80%98Prachanda%E2%80%99)%20has%20been%20lackadaisical%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20supporting%20its%20own%20candidate%2C%20for%20reasons%20that%20will%20become%20clear.%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESelfies%20at%20summits%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Brazen%E2%80%99%20is%20the%20term%20that%20best%20describes%20Hasina%E2%80%99s%20chaperoning%20of%20her%20daughter%20to%20global%20and%20regional%20summits%2C%20misusing%20the%20clout%20that%20comes%20with%20being%20the%20prime%20minister%20of%20a%20country%20as%20important%20as%20Bangladesh.%20The%20nepotism%20cannot%20be%20adding%20to%20the%20stature%20of%20her%20country%20and%20government%2C%20much%20as%20Dahal%E2%80%99s%20unthinking%20actions%20on%20other%20matters%20embarrass%20Nepal%20before%20the%20neighbours%20and%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20it%20is%20nothing%20less%20than%20a%20%E2%80%98South%20Asian%20embarrassment%E2%80%99%20to%20find%20grinning%20photographs%20and%20selfies%20of%20the%20prime%20minister%20and%20first%20daughter%20taken%20over%20the%20last%20few%20months%20with%20President%20Joe%20Biden%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20and%20others.%20Wazed%20was%20right%20up%20there%20by%20her%20mother%E2%80%99s%20side%20hobnobbing%20with%20world%20leaders%20at%20the%20BRICS%20summit%20in%20Johannesburg%2C%20the%20ASEAN%20Summit%20in%20Jakarta%20and%20the%20G-20%20summit%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20besides%20at%20the%20United%20Nations%20General%20Assembly.%20The%20sudden%20escalation%20in%20visibility%20had%20only%20to%20do%20with%20the%20election%20of%20WHO%20regional%20director.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20does%20looks%20like%20the%20WHO-SEARO%20position%20is%20being%20used%20by%20Wazed%20as%20a%20stepping%20stone%20into%20a%20political%20career%20in%20a%20few%20years%E2%80%99%20time.%20There%20is%20talk%20in%20Dhaka%20circles%20that%20Wazed%20is%20being%20groomed%20to%20take%20up%20the%20political%20mantle%20from%20her%20mother%20(and%20grandfather%2C%20the%20assassinated%20Sheikh%20Mujibur%20Rahman)%20instead%20of%20brother%20Sajeeb%20Wazed%20%E2%80%98Joy%E2%80%99%20and%20sister%20Sheikh%20Rehana%20Siddiq.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhichever%20way%20one%20looks%20at%20it%2C%20Hasina%20seems%20to%20be%20using%20the%20WHO%20position%20for%20dynastic%20promotion%2C%20in%20the%20process%20jeopardising%20the%20organisation%20that%20is%20tasked%20with%20watchdogging%20medical%20and%20public%20health%20activities%20of%20hundreds%20of%20millions.%20This%20is%20not%20an%20office%20to%20be%20led%20by%20a%20political%20appointment%20of%20a%20family%20member%2C%20unless%20that%20family%20member%20can%20stand%20full%20scrutiny%20for%20his%2Fher%20skills%20and%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPerusing%20the%20curriculum%20vitae%20of%20Wazed%2C%20appended%20to%20her%20application%20for%20the%20WHO%20position%20and%20available%20online%2C%20she%20seems%20to%20have%20spent%20considerable%20amount%20of%20time%20in%20and%20around%20Barry%20University%20in%20Miami%2C%20Florida.%20(According%20to%20one%20university%20ranking%2C%20the%20university%20is%20placed%20394%20out%20of%20434%20national%20universities%20in%20the%20US%2C%20and%20holds%20the%2021st%C2%A0spot%20for%20Florida.)%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWazed%E2%80%99s%20work%20experience%20has%20been%20mainly%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98licensed%20school%20psychologist%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20Florida%20education%20system.%20Her%20public%20career%20in%20Bangladesh%20seems%20to%20take%20a%20jump%20after%202014.%20While%20one%20should%20not%20even%20think%20of%20undermining%20the%20importance%20of%20her%20activism%20on%20autism%2C%20clearly%20Wazed%E2%80%99s%20positions%20various%20positions%20have%20been%20the%20result%20of%20deft%20backing%20by%20her%20mother%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20with%20conflict%20of%20interest%20writ%20large.%20All%20the%20publications%20cited%20by%20Wazed%20in%20her%20WHO-SEARO%20application%20are%20from%202019%20onwards%20together%20with%20many%20other%20authors%2C%20and%20the%20positions%20she%20mentions%20are%20honorary%20and%20requiring%20irregular%20meetings.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERespected%20international%20medical%20and%20health%20journals%20such%20as%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhealthpolicy-watch.news%2Fshenanigans-in-who-south-east-asia-as-politicians-daughter-contests-for-election-as-regional-director%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%20Health%20Policy%20Watch%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3Eand%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Flancet%2Farticle%2FPIIS0140-6736(23)02026-3%2Ffulltext%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%20The%20Lancet%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20felt%20constrained%20to%20report%20on%20the%20matter%20of%20the%20WHO-SEARO%20elections.%20The%20former%20not%20only%20carried%20a%20report%2C%20but%20also%20editorialised%20on%20the%20matter%20stating%20that%20Hasina%E2%80%99s%20activities%20were%20working%20%E2%80%9Cto%20delegitimise%20both%20the%20election%20process%20and%20the%20future%20credibility%20of%20elected%20WHO%20Regional%20Directors%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWazed%E2%80%99s%20defence%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWazed%20has%20been%20active%20defending%20her%20candidacy%20via%20her%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%20handle%2C%20and%20posting%20endorsements%20that%20come%20mainly%20from%20those%20working%20in%20autism.%20To%20counter%20criticism%2C%20she%20proffers%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Fopinion%2Fbangladesh-pms-daughter-adding-political-colour-to-who-election-she-has-india-on-her-side%2F1791318%2F%5C%22%3Earticle%20from%20the%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Print%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20she%20claims%20%E2%80%9Cdispelled%20the%20campaign%20raised%20by%20%3Cem%3ELancet%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20the%20other%20publications%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20it%20is%20known%20that%20the%20Indian%20government%20has%20not%20disclosed%20its%20preference%20among%20the%20two%20candidates%2C%20the%20puff%20piece%20of%20an%20article%20is%20titled%20%E2%80%9CBangladesh%20PM%E2%80%99s%20daughter%20adding%20political%20colour%20to%20WHO%20elections.%20She%20has%20India%20on%20her%20side.%E2%80%9D%20The%20article%20is%20written%20by%20a%20%E2%80%98former%20journalist%20who%20works%20at%20Chase%20India%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20points%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20Wazed%E2%80%99s%20X%20timeline%20%E2%80%9Cis%20replete%20with%20photos%20with%20the%20who%E2%80%99s%20who%20of%20the%20global%20political%20and%20public%20health%20arena%E2%80%9D%2C%20as%20if%20that%20is%20the%20qualification%20required.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E(The%20use%20of%20%E2%80%98Dr%E2%80%99%20appellation%20in%20Wazed%E2%80%99s%20X%20handle%20may%20be%20questioned%3B%20what%20she%20has%20is%20an%20honorary%20doctorate%20awarded%20in%20early%20March%202023%20by%20the%20Bangabandhu%20Sheikh%20Mujib%20Medical%20University.)%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EResponding%20specifically%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Lancet%3C%2Fem%3E%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ipsnews.net%2F2023%2F10%2Fsetting-record-straight%2F%5C%22%3Espirited%20article%20on%20the%20Inter%20Press%20Service%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20on%20October%209%2C%20Wazed%20said%20she%20was%20being%20targeted%20by%20those%20with%20a%20bias%20against%20the%20field%20of%20psychology.%20Her%20%E2%80%9Cyears%20of%20work%20study%20and%20accomplishments%E2%80%9D%20were%20being%20disregarded%20simply%20because%20she%20is%20daughter%20of%20the%20prime%20minister.%20Wazed%20asks%20that%20her%20professional%20work%20in%20mental%20health%20and%20autism%20be%20counted%2C%20and%20reminds%20readers%20that%20she%20is%20currently%20completing%20a%20doctorate%20in%20education%20in%20organisational%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWazed%20maintains%20that%20opposition%20to%20her%20candidacy%20is%20fuelled%20by%20gender%20discrimination%3A%20%E2%80%9CWomen%20competing%20for%20positions%20of%20power%20in%20major%20institutions%20face%20opposition%20laced%20with%20a%20vicious%20strain%20of%20sexism.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThen%20the%20argument%20takes%20an%20interesting%20turn%3A%20Wazed%20says%20her%20candidacy%20is%20to%20be%20favoured%20vis-%C3%A0-vis%20Acharya%E2%80%99s%20because%2C%20in%20essence%2C%20Bangladesh%20has%20a%20better%20public%20health%20record%20than%20Nepal.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20would%20lead%20to%20a%20more%20reasonable%20consideration%20about%20which%20of%20these%20two%20countries%20has%20better%20public%20health%20outcomes%2C%20and%20therefore%20more%20likely%20to%20make%20better%20choices%20for%20the%20public%20health%20of%20the%20region.%E2%80%9D%20Essentially%2C%20the%20Bangladeshi%20candidate%20equates%20herself%20with%20her%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKathmandu%E2%80%99s%20response%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20position%20of%20the%20Nepali%20government%20leadership%20tends%20sadly%20to%20be%20defined%20by%20real%20or%20imagined%20reading%20of%20what%20New%20Delhi%20wants%2C%20in%20the%20current%20case%2C%20the%20conjecture%20that%20the%20Indian%20government%20favours%20the%20candidacy%20of%20Bangladesh.%20Prime%20Minister%20Dahal%20is%20one%20who%20has%20confided%20that%20Nepal%20should%20have%20a%20government%20that%20is%20%E2%80%98comfortable%E2%80%99%20to%20New%20Delhi%2C%20and%20he%20also%20is%20beholden%20to%20New%20Delhi%20for%20his%20present%20elevation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20circumstances%2C%20on%20numerous%20matters%2C%20the%20Dahal%20government%20wants%20to%20do%20right%20by%20New%20Delhi%2C%20such%20as%20running%20scared%20of%20receiving%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fnepal-india-renew-transit-treaty-sign-deals-in-energy-connectivity%5C%22%3Ereport%20of%20the%20Eminent%20Persons%20Group%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20future%20of%20Nepal-India%20relations%2C%20discussing%20border%20disputes%20or%20asking%20for%20air%20corridors%20over%20Indian%20airspace.%20In%20the%20immediate%20instance%2C%20the%20Dahal%20cabinet%20clearly%20infers%20that%20New%20Delhi%20favours%20Wazed%2C%20based%20on%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20unstinting%20support%20for%20Hasina%E2%80%99s%20government.%20All%20evidence%20points%20to%20the%20Kathmandu%20government%20having%20gone%20cold%20on%20its%20own%20candidate%2C%20which%20is%20why%20foreign%20minister%20N.P.%20Saud%20(of%20the%20Nepali%20Congress)%20was%20most%20unhappy%20when%20a%20Member%20of%20Parliament%20spoke%20in%20support%20of%20Acharya%E2%80%99s%20candidacy%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDhaka%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20is%20emboldened%20by%20the%20Nepali%20government%E2%80%99s%20lack%20of%20enthusiasm%20to%20fight%20the%20good%20fight%20on%20behalf%20of%20Acharya.%20While%20the%20diplomatic%20machinery%20of%20Kathmandu%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20ministry%20is%20held%20in%20check%20by%20the%20Cabinet%2C%20Dhaka%20is%20on%20an%20all-out%20lobbying%20spree%2C%20also%20spreading%20word%20in%20respective%20capitals%20that%20the%20battle%20is%20all%20but%20won.%20Not%20to%20leave%20any%20stone%20unturned%2C%20Bangladesh%20Embassy%20officials%20in%20Kathmandu%20are%20approaching%20local%20journalists%20and%20asking%20them%20to%20write%20articles%20demanding%20a%20retraction%20of%20Acharya%E2%80%99s%20candidacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStatement%20from%20Kathmandu%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20Wazed%20has%20been%20flying%20across%20the%20seven%20seas%20attached%20to%20Hasina%E2%80%99s%20official%20entourage%2C%20Acharya%20has%20to%20contend%20with%20a%20lukewarm%20campaign%20from%20his%20government%2C%20paying%20for%20his%20own%20trips%20to%20Male%2C%20Colombo%2C%20Thimphu%20and%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EClearly%2C%20Hasina%E2%80%99s%20galloping%20authoritarianism%20has%20her%20unable%20to%20restrain%20campaigning%20on%20her%20daughter%E2%80%99s%20behalf.%20The%20sense%20of%20impunity%20and%20invincibility%20is%20seen%20in%20her%20cracking%20down%20on%20independent%20minded%20journalists%20and%20human%20rights%20defenders%2C%20even%20disallowing%20her%20beleaguered%20opponent%20Khaleda%20Zia%20of%20the%20Bangladesh%20Nationalist%20Party%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fbangladesh-govt-refuses-to-allow-jailed-opposition-leader-khaleda-zia-to-travel-for-medical-treatment%5C%22%3Egoing%20overseas%20for%20treatment%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Against%20such%20a%20backdrop%2C%20it%20is%20perhaps%20natural%20that%20there%20is%20little%20or%20no%20dissonance%20in%20Dhaka%20regarding%20Wazed%E2%80%99s%20candidacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlarmed%20by%20the%20strident%20campaign%20of%20the%20Hasina%20government%20for%20the%20secret%20ballot%20that%20is%20to%20be%20held%20in%20late%20October%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20eight%20senior%20Nepali%20civil%20society%20members%20and%20medical%20professionals%20put%20out%20a%20statement%20on%20October%208%2C%20where%20they%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20obvious%20to%20us%20that%20Dr.%20Acharya%20is%20the%20better%20fit%20between%20the%20two%20candidates%20nominated%20for%20the%20position.%20He%20possesses%20a%20strong%20public%20health%20background%20and%20has%20extensive%20leadership%20experience%20in%20tackling%20global%20health%20issues.%20Dr.%20Acharya%20has%20impeccable%20credentials%20with%20a%20PhD%20in%20public%20health%2C%20specialising%20in%20health%20policy%20and%20planning%20from%20a%20globally%20renowned%20university%3B%20a%20Masters%20in%20Sociology%20focusing%20on%20social%20policy%3B%20and%20an%20MBA%20in%20public%20finance%20and%20strategic%20management.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHighlighting%20Acharya%E2%80%99s%20three%20decades%20of%20work%20at%20WHO%2C%20the%20signatories%20add%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20contrast%2C%20the%20only%20other%20candidate%20in%20competition%20for%20the%20position%20is%20regarded%20by%20the%20public%20health%20and%20medical%20fraternity%20as%20a%20political%20prot%C3%A9g%C3%A9%20with%20a%20privileged%20pedigree%20whose%20thin%20resum%C3%A9%20is%20not%20adequate%20to%20lead%20a%20complex%20global%20health%20institution%20such%20as%20WHO-SEARO.%20The%20unabashed%2C%20high-profile%20lobbying%20at%20senior-most%20political%20levels%2C%20aided%20by%20a%20mother%E2%80%99s%20access%20to%20global%20leaders%20at%20unrelated%20summits%20and%20conclaves%2C%20has%20generated%20cautionary%20commentary%20not%20only%20in%20public%20health%20circles%20but%20also%20in%20journals%20of%20renown%20and%20credible%20international%20media.%20In%20the%20current%20post-Covid%20public%20health%20environment%20with%20its%20numerous%20challenges%2C%20UN%20leaders%20steering%20health%20issues%20must%20have%20strong%20credentials%20and%20proven%20dynamism.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDr%20Rita%20Thapa%2C%20one%20of%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20most%20respected%20public%20health%20experts%20with%20half-a-century%E2%80%99s%20contribution%20in%20the%20national%20and%20international%20arena%2C%20who%20has%20worked%20closely%20with%20the%20WHO%20system%2C%20says%3A%20%E2%80%9CWHO%E2%80%99s%20Regional%20Director%20must%20have%20the%20technical%20and%20managerial%20competencies%20to%20promote%2C%20restore%20and%20maintain%20health%20in%20the%20member%20states.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAdds%20Thapa%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20would%20be%20shameful%20to%20have%20leadership%20in%20WHO-SEARO%20without%20adequate%20qualifications%2C%20which%20would%20limit%20the%20objectives%20of%20global%20health.%E2%80%9D%20She%20asks%20that%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20WHO%20Regional%20Committee%2C%20health%20minister%20of%20Bhutan%20Dechen%20Wangmo%20%E2%80%9Cundertake%20rigorous%20validation%20of%20the%20qualifications%2C%20competencies%20and%20claims%20of%20candidates%2C%20and%20ensure%20greater%20transparency%20in%20the%20selection%20process%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20public%20health%20and%20medical%20challenges%20faced%20by%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20people%20in%20the%20South%20and%20Southeast%20Asian%20region%2C%20with%20more%20dangers%20looming%20in%20the%20form%20of%20new%20vectors%20and%20variants%2C%20amidst%20transforming%20climate%20and%20escalating%20income%20disparities%20resulting%20in%20poor%20spread%20of%20public%20services%20%E2%80%93%20the%20importance%20of%20the%20watchdogging%20and%20guidance%20functions%20of%20the%20regional%20director%20of%20WHO%20cannot%20be%20underestimated.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20will%20be%20for%20the%2011%20government%20representatives%2C%20when%20they%20gather%20to%20vote%2C%20to%20consider%20neither%20the%20vehement%20lobbying%20by%20the%20Bangladeshi%20prime%20pinister%20nor%20the%20careful%20silence%20of%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20prime%20minister.%20They%20should%20simply%20keep%20in%20mind%20the%20best%20interests%20of%20the%20public%20of%20the%20vast%20and%20variegated%20region%2C%20in%20individual%20countries%20large%20and%20small%20as%20well%20as%20cumulatively.%20This%20will%20require%20looking%20at%20the%20work%20experience%20of%20the%20two%20candidates%20and%20dispassionately%20deciding%20who%20should%20get%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKanak%20Mani%20Dixit%20is%20the%20publisher%20of%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0Himal%20Khabarpatrika%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eand%20the%20founding%20editor%20of%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.himalmag.com%2F%5C%22%3EHimal%20Southasian%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697104839000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12140159%2FF6jsHPjacAA7LFS.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fsheikh-hasina-and-the-question-of-nepotism%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Bangladesh%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20fervent%20lobbying%20for%20her%20daughter%20to%20head%20the%20World%20Health%20Organisation%E2%80%99s%20regional%20office%20jeopardises%20its%20status%20as%20a%20monitor%20of%20public%20health%20in%20a%20region%20that%20includes%20India%20and%20contains%20a%20fourth%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20population.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A13%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fsheikh-hasina-and-the-question-of-nepotism%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Stop%2C%20we%20don't%20want%20this!'%3A%20Pupils%20shown%20Winnie%20the%20Pooh%20themed%20horror%20film%20by%20teacher%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697103780000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F10%2F768x432%2Fskynews-winnie-the-pooh-blood-and-honey_6319073.jpg%3F20231012113501%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fmiami-school-receives-complaints-after-pupils-shown-winnie-the-pooh-themed-horror-film-by-teacher-12983060%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20school%20in%20Miami%2C%20